00:28:12.975 --> 00:28:20.168
have gathered since. There are various bestiaries
and gatherings of information about the dangerous

00:28:20.168 --> 00:28:24.352
denizens in the countryside around you, and it is
a very dangerous place outside of the few points

00:28:24.352 --> 00:28:27.990
of civilized society that has built up its own
defenses.

00:28:27.990 --> 00:28:33.767
Throughout the evening and the morning, you've
managed to find eventually a piece that talks

00:28:33.767 --> 00:28:40.298
about various undead entities and the process of
undeath, and necromantic magics that have been

00:28:40.298 --> 00:28:48.167
perverted throughout the generations to defy the
natural cycle of life. You do come across an entry

00:28:48.167 --> 00:28:55.469
about vampirism. It is extremely rare and was
largely thought abolished close to 200 years ago.

00:28:55.469 --> 00:29:02.565
There are very rare whispers of any sort of cases
out there, and usually as soon as something comes

00:29:02.565 --> 00:29:12.038
to any sort of public knowledge, large mobs gather
and whoever was infected with this horrible state

00:29:12.038 --> 00:29:14.355
was hunted down and killed.

00:29:14.355 --> 00:29:21.558
What you do learn from this is religious
symbology, while classically thought to have an

00:29:21.558 --> 00:29:26.649
effect on people afflicted with vampirism,
actually has no effect. It's more of a

00:29:26.649 --> 00:29:33.577
superstition, but does not actually have any
negative impact on the individual. However,

00:29:33.577 --> 00:29:46.010
certain things that do render a vampire easier to
destroy: the presence of sunlight. Anything that

00:29:46.010 --> 00:29:50.537
counts as sunlight can damage them progressively
the longer they're in it, prevent them from

00:29:50.537 --> 00:29:56.405
restoring their health, and ultimately destroy
them and turn them to ash, should they be brought

00:29:56.405 --> 00:30:02.179
to the brink of death in the presence of sunlight.
Also, very quickly and consistently rushing

00:30:02.179 --> 00:30:11.856
water. Being held into a rushing stream or under a
waterfall would have a similar effect to sunlight.

00:30:11.856 --> 00:30:19.330
You do also know the stake in the heart is also
considered to be a way to destroy them. It does

00:30:19.330 --> 00:30:24.149
not actually destroy them, but it does render them
paralyzed and has to be done when they're in their

00:30:24.149 --> 00:30:33.060
resting place, within their coffin and/or the dirt
that is considered their resting location. Usually

00:30:33.060 --> 00:30:37.708
that is the beginning step: to find and locate
where the vampire is resting, stake in the heart,

00:30:37.708 --> 00:30:41.769
and then carry the body to sunlight or rushing
water. And that's how they're permanently

00:30:41.769 --> 00:30:45.681
destroyed. You also find out that if a vampire is
thought to be killed under any other

00:30:45.681 --> 00:30:51.158
circumstances, the body turns to mist and is nigh
invulnerable and eventually finds its way back to

00:30:51.158 --> 00:30:55.412
wherever they've hidden their resting place to
recover within a very short period of time, making

00:30:55.412 --> 00:30:59.864
them extremely dangerous, unless you have the
right situation, the right conditions, to bring

00:30:59.864 --> 00:31:02.679
them to that point. So that information is now at
your disposal.

00:31:02.679 --> 00:31:05.835
ORION: Wonderful.

