LAURA: Yes. Tiberius, the point of this is you
killed an old woman last night, very brutally.

00:34:31.690 --> 00:34:34.297
Please maybe don't do that again.

00:34:34.297 --> 00:34:38.501
ORION: She felt nothing, but of course. And I was
giving my new Krull blade a good old try.

00:34:38.501 --> 00:34:44.314
LAURA: Yes, you were. Maybe not on sleeping people
anymore. People who are actually attacking us.

00:34:44.314 --> 00:34:47.254
ORION: She was-- okay, fine.

00:34:47.254 --> 00:34:59.286
LIAM: Well, I think the point is your abilities in
arcane wonder are expanding daily. Exponentially.

00:34:59.286 --> 00:35:04.878
And perhaps be a little tentative. Do a little
practice run in the woods on your own, once in

00:35:04.878 --> 00:35:08.999
a while, and see what the effects are before you go
whipping it out.

00:35:08.999 --> 00:35:10.982
ORION: Are there woods nearby?

00:35:10.982 --> 00:35:18.722
SAM: This is an intervention. We love you very
much, but you killed an old lady.

00:35:18.722 --> 00:35:20.659
TRAVIS: I like the way you kill people.

00:35:20.659 --> 00:35:22.508
ORION: Well, yes.

00:35:22.508 --> 00:35:24.744
LAURA: We're all on the up and up now, right?

00:35:24.744 --> 00:35:28.138
ORION: One raises a hand to me or Vox Machina,
they are going to die.

00:35:28.138 --> 00:35:29.788
TRAVIS: Yeah! Yeah, they are!

00:35:29.788 --> 00:35:33.059
ORION: It is simple. I do not know why this is a
discussion. I won't be as cruel--

00:35:33.059 --> 00:35:40.192
MARISHA: You know, she didn't even really do
anything. She was really old.

00:35:40.192 --> 00:35:41.807
LAURA: She was attacking us.

00:35:41.807 --> 00:35:43.226
LIAM: Keyleth.

00:35:43.226 --> 00:35:44.715
MARISHA: What?

00:35:44.715 --> 00:35:50.796
LIAM: Clearly, we all love you as family, and
nobody blames you, but you once killed a child,

00:35:50.796 --> 00:35:52.954
and none of us blame you for that.

00:35:52.954 --> 00:35:56.373
TRAVIS: Is it too early to start drinking? I pull
out the cask of ale.

00:35:56.373 --> 00:35:58.652
LIAM: And that happened in the heat of battle.

00:35:58.652 --> 00:36:04.423
MARISHA: You know, I'm really sensitive about
that, Vax. I'm &lt;i&gt;really&lt;/i&gt; sensitive about that,

00:36:04.423 --> 00:36:05.425
Vax!

00:36:05.425 --> 00:36:06.825
LIAM: I'm well aware.

00:36:06.825 --> 00:36:10.377
MARISHA: And that was different.

00:36:10.377 --> 00:36:12.456
LAURA: It was an accident!

00:36:12.456 --> 00:36:16.134
MARISHA: That was pretty fucking deliberate, what
he did.

00:36:16.134 --> 00:36:21.472
ORION: Yes, to someone who was opposing us. That
was a child who was innocent. Or was he opposing

00:36:21.472 --> 00:36:23.309
us, too? I don't remember, actually.

00:36:23.309 --> 00:36:25.094
LIAM: And it all falls apart.

00:36:25.094 --> 00:36:28.293
MARISHA: He was being puppeted by sorcerer Michael
Jackson.

00:36:28.293 --> 00:36:36.580
LIAM: No one agrees with you today more than I,
and I think we can adjust our perspective

00:36:36.580 --> 00:36:38.074
slightly. Right, Grog?

00:36:38.074 --> 00:36:39.732
TRAVIS: What's the word?

00:36:39.732 --> 00:36:41.039
LIAM: See?

00:36:41.039 --> 00:36:42.794
SAM: Kill softer.

00:36:42.794 --> 00:36:46.440
ORION: I'll show you how. You just have to do it
really slow.

00:36:46.440 --> 00:36:50.147
LAURA: Uriel's waiting for us.

00:36:50.147 --> 00:36:57.836
SAM: Let's table this. We'll stick a pin in this
discussion. We'll all be thinking long and hard

00:36:57.836 --> 00:36:58.849
about this.

00:36:58.849 --> 00:37:00.933
LAURA: Keyleth, it wasn't intentional and
everybody knows that.

00:37:00.933 --> 00:37:02.928
LIAM: Absolutely. Not intentional. No.

00:37:02.928 --> 00:37:06.143
MARISHA: I turn into Minxie and start walking.

00:37:06.143 --> 00:37:10.512
TRAVIS: Minxie! I go and give a little scratch
behind the ears.

00:37:10.512 --> 00:37:13.474
MATT: You guys gather and make your way into the
city of Emon proper.

00:37:13.474 --> 00:37:20.494
LAURA: Actually, before we head towards Uriel, we
probably should-- do we have any sort of proof

00:37:20.494 --> 00:37:25.176
that the Briarwoods actually did horrible things
and it wasn't us attacking them?

00:37:25.176 --> 00:37:27.524
LIAM: Well, I've got these little scars right
here.

00:37:27.524 --> 00:37:31.329
MATT: The scars are still there. They're still
wounds that are healing.

00:37:31.329 --> 00:37:38.503
LAURA: All right. Cool. Just making sure that we
had something.

00:37:38.503 --> 00:37:41.473
LIAM: And then there was what's-his-name, Awesome
Pants, who was there.

00:37:41.473 --> 00:37:43.227
LAURA: Seeker Asum.

00:37:43.227 --> 00:37:45.059
ORION: Allura saw everything, as well.

00:37:45.059 --> 00:37:46.719
SAM: Did she see the fight?

00:37:46.719 --> 00:37:48.324
LAURA: Allura didn't see the fight.

00:37:48.324 --> 00:37:55.034
LIAM: We know she knows what's up, but whether she
can be used as a reliable witness is-- we've got

00:37:55.034 --> 00:37:57.424
multiple witnesses.

00:37:57.424 --> 00:38:01.228
SAM: There were those guards, too. There was
guards outside the door.

00:38:01.228 --> 00:38:02.927
LIAM: They were incinerated.

00:38:02.927 --> 00:38:04.261
SAM: Oh yeah.

00:38:04.261 --> 00:38:06.409
LAURA: Plus, they were the Briarwoods' guards,
anyway.

00:38:06.409 --> 00:38:08.070
ORION: One of them was still alive. I didn't kill
both of them.

00:38:08.070 --> 00:38:10.229
LAURA: He went away with the Briarwoods, I'm going
to assume.

00:38:10.229 --> 00:38:13.964
TRAVIS: What a dick! We go to see Uriel.

00:38:13.964 --> 00:38:15.624
MATT: Okay.

00:38:15.624 --> 00:38:20.462
TRAVIS: I made a choice for the team!

00:38:20.462 --> 00:38:24.313
(laughter)

00:38:24.313 --> 00:38:29.982
MATT: As you're having this discussion, all of you
make your way into the city of Emon, across the

00:38:29.982 --> 00:38:34.292
districts to the Cloudtop. You're greeted and let
within the gate into the central district there.

00:38:34.292 --> 00:38:40.506
You make your way to the palace of Tal'Dorei,
through the front doors. The guards that are there

00:38:40.506 --> 00:38:46.947
lead you in and one of them says, "Uriel is
waiting within the throne chamber." You guys are

00:38:46.947 --> 00:38:49.552
led down the main hallway into the very center of
the palace.

00:38:49.552 --> 00:38:51.964
MARISHA: I come out of Minxie.

00:38:51.964 --> 00:38:57.605
MATT: The nervous guard, thankfully, puts his
weapon away and is like, "Oh! Lady Keyleth, my

00:38:57.605 --> 00:38:59.941
"apologies." And puts his spear to the side.

00:38:59.941 --> 00:39:02.142
LAURA: Trinket's still here, though.

00:39:02.142 --> 00:39:09.059
LIAM: I buzz over to that specific guard and say,
do you have a lost and found here? I have this

00:39:09.059 --> 00:39:15.920
really badass serpent-style belt. Sometimes it
crawls around on its own. Sometimes it's just a

00:39:15.920 --> 00:39:21.429
belt. And I lost it here the other night. And I'm
really hoping-- I mean, it ties everything

00:39:21.429 --> 00:39:24.569
together. Is there anyone I can check with?

00:39:24.569 --> 00:39:31.458
MATT: "Check back after you've spoken with the
Sovereign, please. Thank you." Leads you guys on.

00:39:31.458 --> 00:39:35.713
As you head down the main hallway-- and you recall
this hallway. This was a long, dangerous trek the

00:39:35.713 --> 00:39:39.449
first time you came to the palace. This was where
Uriel's family was possessed. This is where you

00:39:39.449 --> 00:39:45.316
had your battle with the glabrezu. This is where
Pike was slain. This is where you had to pull the

00:39:45.316 --> 00:39:50.218
shadows from the bodies of his family. This is a
very emotional place that you really haven't been

00:39:50.218 --> 00:39:58.832
to since that sequence of events. Walking in
already has this tenuous state of low-simmering

00:39:58.832 --> 00:40:03.958
energy. As you're brought into the main chamber,
you can see there is the dual thrones for Uriel

00:40:03.958 --> 00:40:07.432
and his wife. His wife is not present; his family
is not present, just Uriel sitting on the throne.

00:40:07.432 --> 00:40:12.578
There are a few guards on the different entrances
to the room. As you walk in, Uriel just sits there

00:40:12.578 --> 00:40:18.371
on the throne and gives you acknowledgment and
ushers you into the room. You all step in. Trinket

00:40:18.371 --> 00:40:22.845
behind you keeping an eye out. Like a bear is wont
to do.

00:40:22.845 --> 00:40:30.408
You guys make your way up towards the very edge of
the central raised dais where the thrones are

00:40:30.408 --> 00:40:38.332
currently set up on. You now see on the opposite
side of the room, Seeker Asum and Allura walk in,

00:40:38.332 --> 00:40:45.654
as well as Arbiter Brom, who is the cleric that is
the Master of Law in the city. They walk up and

00:40:45.654 --> 00:40:52.020
flank the sides of the throne, stepping back a
little bit to not gather all the attention, but

00:40:52.020 --> 00:40:59.881
definitely be there as a show of support. As they
enter, the doors on the other side of the room and the

00:40:59.881 --> 00:41:07.821
door behind you open, and roughly 30 guards enter
the chamber quietly. They all filter in, blocking

00:41:07.821 --> 00:41:14.826
all the exits. The doors close. No weapons are
drawn, but there is a very strong showing of

00:41:14.826 --> 00:41:18.500
muscle in this room that you weren't expecting for
this meeting.

00:41:18.500 --> 00:41:24.599
Once all the guards are settled and a really
awkward silence hits the room, Uriel stands up

00:41:24.599 --> 00:41:34.263
from the throne and looks upon you. Pacing
slightly, back and forth. "Thank you all for

00:41:34.263 --> 00:41:42.869
"joining me. I must say, I am troubled by recent
events, and I wish to speak to you regarding them

00:41:42.869 --> 00:41:51.651
"before taking any action. I owe you that much for
all you've done for me. Before you left for

00:41:51.651 --> 00:42:01.372
"Vasselheim, you showed immediate interest in the
Briarwoods. Percy in-- Where is Percival?"

00:42:01.372 --> 00:42:12.280
SAM: Well, he's not feeling well today after the
events of last night, so he stayed behind.

00:42:12.280 --> 00:42:22.723
MATT: "Well, then please relay this conversation
to him as soon as you see him. You exhibited

00:42:22.723 --> 00:42:28.469
"interest in the Briarwoods before leaving for
Vasselheim. I, through trust, did not inquire as

00:42:28.469 --> 00:42:34.232
"to why. But upon your return, eagerly told you
they were coming to this feast and invited you as

00:42:34.232 --> 00:42:39.078
"part of the Council of Tal'Dorei to join this
feast, as it was your request. I graciously

00:42:39.078 --> 00:42:45.302
"followed through. You showed up. A meal was had.
Questions were asked, although curious ones; I did

00:42:45.302 --> 00:42:55.831
"not pry. Now I have since been notified, and seen
a bit of the aftermath, that you, Vox Machina,

00:42:55.831 --> 00:43:07.153
"seemingly attacked our guests shortly-- please.
Listen. Attacked our guests shortly after the meal

00:43:07.153 --> 00:43:13.754
"in their own guest quarters. Forcing them to flee,
after you destroyed the hallway, ruined their

00:43:13.754 --> 00:43:22.611
"carriage, murdered two of their guards, two more
outside, and leaving Seeker Asum to witness this

00:43:22.611 --> 00:43:30.700
"entire process." Asum gives a nod. "You then
tortured their carriage driver, requested he be

00:43:30.700 --> 00:43:36.081
"sent to the dungeon beneath your keep. And upon my
sentries returning from Greyskull to deliver him,

00:43:36.081 --> 00:43:43.084
"they find a freshly murdered old woman not far
behind the path you took. Not long after, Seeker

00:43:43.084 --> 00:43:48.852
"Asum found me and corroborated most of this
unexpected, violent behavior. I then asked Arbiter

00:43:48.852 --> 00:43:54.775
"Brom here to divine the nature of this murder. And
through his divine sight, through the goddess

00:43:54.775 --> 00:44:00.923
"Ioun, comes to tell me it was none other than you,
Tiberius, that slaughtered this elderly woman

00:44:00.923 --> 00:44:02.738
"while she slept."

00:44:02.738 --> 00:44:05.195
ORION: Yes!

00:44:05.195 --> 00:44:10.734
MATT: "Now, I am quite disturbed by the events of
these past 14 hours, and I would like to hear an

00:44:10.734 --> 00:44:17.289
"explanation. Arbiter, if you could please, prepare
the space." Arbiter Brom steps forward and

00:44:17.289 --> 00:44:22.196
pulls forth from underneath his robes a necklace
that contains a holy symbol. The same symbol you

00:44:22.196 --> 00:44:30.343
saw across the temple beneath the Slayer's Take,
an eye-like inscription of the god Ioun. Brom

00:44:30.343 --> 00:44:37.139
grasps it, looks about you all, and prepares this
slight hand gesture, and you feel a slight tingle

00:44:37.139 --> 00:44:39.460
across the skin that lasts a few seconds.

00:44:39.460 --> 00:44:41.773
MARISHA: Can I recognize the spell he's casting?

00:44:41.773 --> 00:44:44.864
MATT: I'll say go ahead and make a-- this would be
a religion check.

00:44:44.864 --> 00:44:52.918
MARISHA: He's doing a cleric thing, yeah? Seven.

00:44:52.918 --> 00:45:00.544
MATT: All right. Unable to ascertain the nature.
However, the incantation completes. No seeming

00:45:00.544 --> 00:45:07.999
noticeable effect. Brom nods and steps back in the
line of the thrones. I want all of you guys to

00:45:07.999 --> 00:45:10.538
roll charisma saving throws.

00:45:10.538 --> 00:45:15.095
MARISHA: Son of a bitch. Always a problem.

00:45:15.095 --> 00:45:21.747
ORION: 19.

00:45:21.747 --> 00:45:23.309
MARISHA: 11.

00:45:23.309 --> 00:45:29.215
SAM: I get advantage, and I rolled a 27.

00:45:29.215 --> 00:45:31.772
MATT: (laughs) Okay. Bards.

00:45:31.772 --> 00:45:33.132
LIAM: 19.

00:45:33.132 --> 00:45:34.640
LAURA: 13.

00:45:34.640 --> 00:45:35.965
TRAVIS: 18.

00:45:35.965 --> 00:45:45.212
MATT: All right. Good to know. Uriel then looks to
the rest of you. "So. I've said my piece for the

00:45:45.212 --> 00:45:47.795
"moment. Explain."

00:45:47.795 --> 00:45:49.720
LIAM: I step forward.

00:45:49.720 --> 00:45:57.859
MARISHA: Can I do a quick insight check on Asum to
see if I can still recognize if he's still

00:45:57.859 --> 00:46:01.134
affected by the mind-control thing?

00:46:01.134 --> 00:46:04.562
MATT: Go ahead and make an insight check, sure.

00:46:04.562 --> 00:46:09.989
MARISHA: Ooh yeah! 28.

00:46:09.989 --> 00:46:18.159
MATT: Glancing at Asum, the way he's looking at
you and the general tension and feeling of the

00:46:18.159 --> 00:46:28.617
room, you gather that Asum is not his normal self
completely. You step forward.

00:46:28.617 --> 00:46:37.532
LIAM: Uriel. With all respect, I needn't remind
you what the group of people before you put

00:46:37.532 --> 00:46:43.499
themselves through on your behalf and your
family's behalf. We almost lost one of our own.

00:46:43.499 --> 00:46:50.474
And if that counts for nothing here, then nothing
makes sense. But if that is not enough, let us

00:46:50.474 --> 00:46:53.251
start here.

00:46:53.251 --> 00:47:01.481
ORION: The Briarwoods are vampires. And that old
lady, who was a butthole by the way, was with this

00:47:01.481 --> 00:47:04.362
demonoid person who we had to fight as well.

00:47:04.362 --> 00:47:13.095
LIAM: One thing at a time. That's true, but one
thing at a time. We had prior knowledge of the

00:47:13.095 --> 00:47:20.544
Briarwoods' intentions before this evening. And I
myself went to spy on them.

00:47:20.544 --> 00:47:28.591
LAURA: Here's the thing. Percy doesn't like them
because they killed his family. They took over his

00:47:28.591 --> 00:47:38.555
home, after killing his family. He got away. He
knows they're scary. We're trying to protect you.

00:47:38.555 --> 00:47:43.554
ORION: So the point is, we all know how dangerous
it is that the knowledge of vampire existence and

00:47:43.554 --> 00:47:50.201
the spreading of those vile creatures. And now we
know they do exist. So however the means that that

00:47:50.201 --> 00:47:54.884
came about is neither here nor there. We know
where they are.

00:47:54.884 --> 00:48:00.346
TRAVIS: And if you're wondering how we know
they're vampires-- (whispering) Vax, this is your

00:48:00.346 --> 00:48:01.446
cue.

00:48:01.446 --> 00:48:12.571
LIAM: I will subject myself to any test, to any
wizard or mage in this city who you know can

00:48:12.571 --> 00:48:18.659
ascertain the truth. To look through my eyes, to
see my memories. I don't know shit about magic,

00:48:18.659 --> 00:48:20.444
but there are people who do.

00:48:20.444 --> 00:48:28.723
SAM: Cleric Tristan also treated him last night
for his vampire-inflicted wound. I know this all

00:48:28.723 --> 00:48:34.106
looks really bad on the surface, and we did not
want to cause any disturbance within these

00:48:34.106 --> 00:48:42.549
hallowed walls, but there was a danger, we acted.
Perhaps too abruptly and without telling you.

00:48:42.549 --> 00:48:47.960
LAURA: We tried to get your attention. I called
for you immediately. As soon as we knew there was

00:48:47.960 --> 00:48:49.255
danger.

00:48:49.255 --> 00:48:53.056
LIAM: And don't take our word for it. Anyone, have
them look in here.

00:48:53.056 --> 00:48:55.533
ORION: Actually, you take a Stormwind's word for--

00:48:55.533 --> 00:49:09.081
MATT: "Silence! Silence. You're in my court now,
Stormwind. You put so much weight upon this trust,

00:49:09.081 --> 00:49:14.598
"and you have done a good service. But also I've
heard whispers that you've thrown this trust

00:49:14.598 --> 00:49:20.841
"around in many circles. Remember, we held a parade
in your honor; we spread the word of the good

00:49:20.841 --> 00:49:26.918
"deeds you've done. We, at our own costs of Emon,
built you a keep, a home, at great expense, to

00:49:26.918 --> 00:49:35.526
"show thanks. And also, I believed, upon allowing
you to join the council, put us square. I owe you

00:49:35.526 --> 00:49:38.444
"nothing. Just as you owe me nothing."

00:49:38.444 --> 00:49:40.369
LIAM: Do you not want the truth?

00:49:40.369 --> 00:49:46.159
MATT: "I want the truth, but I also want you to
understand the stakes that are here and why there

00:49:46.159 --> 00:49:54.277
"is this question. As the leader of this-- not this
city, but this entire countryside, I have to be

00:49:54.277 --> 00:50:01.728
"sure, and this is not the first time I have been
lied to by very close, trusted people, so I have

00:50:01.728 --> 00:50:03.138
"to be thorough."

00:50:03.138 --> 00:50:10.890
LIAM: This is why I offer myself completely into
your control and put myself under your supervision

00:50:10.890 --> 00:50:17.531
and any user of the arcane arts you want to 
peer inside my mind, let them step up to the

00:50:17.531 --> 00:50:19.812
plate, because I have nothing to hide.

00:50:19.812 --> 00:50:26.157
LAURA: Also, while you are inquiring about him,
you might inquire about Seeker Asum.

00:50:26.157 --> 00:50:30.500
SAM: If you're worried about lies within your own
ranks, I think you should start with him.

00:50:30.500 --> 00:50:36.681
MARISHA: In fact, I actually might be able to help
Seeker Asum, if you will allow me to.

00:50:36.681 --> 00:50:38.180
SAM: Help him?

00:50:38.180 --> 00:50:42.113
MATT: You glance over at Asum, and Asum gives a
look to Uriel and Uriel--

00:50:42.113 --> 00:50:45.238
LAURA: He was mind-controlled last night.

00:50:45.238 --> 00:50:54.756
MATT: "I have had Asum at my side for the better
part of 15 years. He is responsible, far more than

00:50:54.756 --> 00:51:01.586
"your merry band has ever attempted, for keeping
and maintaining the good and lawful state of this

00:51:01.586 --> 00:51:02.490
"country."

00:51:02.490 --> 00:51:15.003
LIAM: Uriel, your own family was not themselves!
And you know that! Look into my mind! Now! Today!

00:51:15.003 --> 00:51:17.733
You don't need to guess anything.

00:51:17.733 --> 00:51:32.422
MATT: "It would also do you well to show respect.
We are speaking, half-elf. Now, I would assign

00:51:32.422 --> 00:51:40.940
"Allura to such an endeavor. However, it has also
been noticed that she has grown quite friendly and

00:51:40.940 --> 00:51:49.702
"attached to your group, and in this circumstance,
there is question. So you will be, in a few days,

00:51:49.702 --> 00:51:53.499
"assigned an individual to this ritual of which you
are presenting yourself."

00:51:53.499 --> 00:51:55.616
MARISHA: Uriel, please--

00:51:55.616 --> 00:52:07.981
MATT: "Shh. The Briarwoods, regardless of what
you may think they may be, or we do-- that will

00:52:07.981 --> 00:52:15.974
"show in time-- have shown nothing over the past
five years but graciousness, and gone through all

00:52:15.974 --> 00:52:21.696
"proper channels to establish this relationship
between our city and theirs. Far more than the

00:52:21.696 --> 00:52:24.320
"previous family ever attempted."

00:52:24.320 --> 00:52:32.432
LIAM: Well, one may smile and smile and still be a
villain.

00:52:32.432 --> 00:52:38.961
MATT: "That goes both ways. Now, please."

00:52:38.961 --> 00:52:49.964
MARISHA: Just let me do a quick restoration spell
on Asum. If nothing is wrong with him, nothing

00:52:49.964 --> 00:52:59.705
will happen. It's harmless. It's like taking
medicine when you're not sick. It can't hurt. And

00:52:59.705 --> 00:53:10.395
if I am wrong, then we can continue on. We can
have Vax tested. Please, it'll take ten minutes.

00:53:10.395 --> 00:53:12.029
What can it hurt?

00:53:12.029 --> 00:53:16.229
LAURA: Up until last night, he was himself. Trust
us that now he is not.

00:53:16.229 --> 00:53:17.757
MARISHA: He came to us.

00:53:17.757 --> 00:53:24.020
MATT: "There has been nothing about his behavior,
at all, to insinuate any change of anything of the

00:53:24.166 --> 00:53:32.725
"sort. And I have known the man for quite some
time, before I even took this throne. However, I

00:53:32.725 --> 00:53:39.480
"will, in the good graces and the relationship we
forged, allow this. Asum, are you all right with

00:53:39.480 --> 00:53:40.347
"this?"

00:53:40.347 --> 00:53:46.054
Asum gives a nod. "Well, if this is to be how it
is. Certainly." And he steps forward. The halfling

00:53:46.054 --> 00:53:51.678
approaches you, looking you in the face. All
right. You would like to attempt your Greater

00:53:51.678 --> 00:53:53.279
Restoration spell?

00:53:53.279 --> 00:53:57.879
MARISHA: First, I meditate for a second, and I
cast Enhance Ability on myself.

00:53:57.879 --> 00:54:02.861
MATT: As a note, as you begin casting, you notice
the guards all go for their weapons and ready

00:54:02.861 --> 00:54:08.407
themselves, uncertain of what's about to
transpire. There is a tension in the room based on

00:54:08.407 --> 00:54:11.671
what this is going to be.

00:54:11.671 --> 00:54:15.812
MARISHA: Can I get some meditation music,
Scanlan?

00:54:15.812 --> 00:54:32.894
SAM: Oh! (chanting)

00:54:32.894 --> 00:54:35.195
MATT: All right. So first you cast Enhance Ability
on yourself.

00:54:35.195 --> 00:54:37.582
MARISHA: Am I maybe inspired by that?

00:54:37.582 --> 00:54:46.398
MATT: Sure. In the tension of the room, this slow
droning hum of the gnome, which you can notice

00:54:46.398 --> 00:54:53.230
some of the guards look at each other, confused.
And Asum puts his hand up like, hold off.

00:54:53.230 --> 00:54:55.809
LIAM: It's Tuvan throat singing.

00:54:55.809 --> 00:55:02.760
MATT: All right. So first you cast Enhance
Ability on your--

00:55:02.760 --> 00:55:04.252
MARISHA: Self.

00:55:04.252 --> 00:55:06.177
SAM: What ability?

00:55:06.177 --> 00:55:16.949
MARISHA: To enhance wisdom? Wisdom.

00:55:16.949 --> 00:55:26.715
MATT: Okay. You reach out with Greater
Restoration. You complete the ritual. You touch

00:55:26.715 --> 00:55:35.836
onto the arms of Asum. It fades, and you see in
his eyes there's a moment of clarity and an

00:55:35.836 --> 00:55:45.260
inhale. A slight gasp, like some realization hits
him and his expression changes and looks towards

00:55:45.260 --> 00:55:53.562
you and just goes-- He puts his hands out like
this for a moment, just trying to almost tell you

00:55:53.562 --> 00:55:58.539
something. Go ahead and make a wisdom check. Just
a d20. Or no, make an insight. Make a straight

00:55:58.539 --> 00:56:00.961
insight. This is more of an insight roll here.

00:56:00.961 --> 00:56:04.700
MARISHA: Okay. Oh! 29.

00:56:04.700 --> 00:56:10.761
MATT: You get the sense through the subtlety of
physical motion and expression, Asum is telling

00:56:10.761 --> 00:56:21.343
you, just go with me on this. He steps back into
the place next to the throne. There's a brief

00:56:21.343 --> 00:56:26.740
moment of pause. Uriel says, "And, Asum?"

00:56:26.740 --> 00:56:32.944
Asum goes, "My stance has not changed. I know not
what she is attempting or thought the situation

00:56:32.944 --> 00:56:38.751
"was, but it appears to me that this was either
misinformation or at least at the time being,

00:56:38.751 --> 00:56:43.455
"hopefully, not a lie. But I believe Brom has taken
care of that, yes?"

00:56:43.455 --> 00:56:46.897
And Brom gives a nod. "I certainly have hoped
to."

00:56:46.897 --> 00:57:03.253
Uriel goes, "Hm. All right. Here's the
circumstance: as it stands, I fear I must revoke

00:57:03.253 --> 00:57:10.201
"Vox Machina's membership in the council of
Tal'Dorei until further notice, for the safety of

00:57:10.201 --> 00:57:19.291
"our countryside and the current tension in our
relationship."

00:57:19.291 --> 00:57:27.057
SAM: Objection! That's it. I just wanted to say
that. Please continue. I just want it noted that

00:57:27.057 --> 00:57:29.524
we object strongly to this.

00:57:29.524 --> 00:57:37.267
MATT: "I understand. And this will only continue
until all of our investigations are complete."

00:57:37.267 --> 00:57:45.093
SAM: Are we still allowed free rein to roam about
as we please? Are we under arrest for anything?

00:57:45.093 --> 00:57:50.529
MATT: "You are not under arrest. You are revoked
from the council, and you will be closely watched

00:57:50.529 --> 00:57:53.232
"until our investigations are complete."

00:57:53.232 --> 00:57:56.530
LAURA: How long will your investigations take?

00:57:56.530 --> 00:58:03.528
MATT: He looks back to Asum and Asum says, "Well,
depends on how quickly we can acquire the

00:58:03.528 --> 00:58:08.686
"information; it could be weeks. I'll do my best to
make it thorough and quick."

00:58:08.686 --> 00:58:11.135
LAURA: Are we allowed to leave the city in that
time?

00:58:11.135 --> 00:58:17.695
MATT: Uriel looks back and says, "You may leave if
you wish. Know that there have been precautions

00:58:17.695 --> 00:58:22.494
"taken. Should you attempt to flee, we will find
you."

00:58:22.494 --> 00:58:24.863
LIAM: And when are you to look into my mind?

00:58:24.863 --> 00:58:27.956
LAURA: Weirdo!

00:58:27.956 --> 00:58:31.651
(laughter)

00:58:31.651 --> 00:58:33.578
LIAM: It freaking ends here. Right away.

00:58:33.578 --> 00:58:35.394
TRAVIS: Can you read my mind?

00:58:35.394 --> 00:58:36.999
LIAM: There is no spoon.

00:58:36.999 --> 00:58:44.525
MATT: "We ought to speak to the Lyceum to find a
proper individual of sufficient power and trust to

00:58:44.525 --> 00:58:50.297
"do this, as Allura right now is being kept out of
the scenario."

00:58:50.297 --> 00:58:54.359
SAM: Are we allowed to speak with Allura?

00:58:54.359 --> 00:59:01.805
MATT: "If you wish. Outside of these chambers. Do
what you must to clear your name. I would like

00:59:01.805 --> 00:59:10.646
"very much for this all to be true, what you're
saying. But do not flee. Do not give an

00:59:10.646 --> 00:59:14.789
"inclination that you attempt to escape this
judgment, for we will take that as a sign of

00:59:14.789 --> 00:59:16.186
"guilt."

00:59:16.186 --> 00:59:18.857
LIAM: We've no intention of going anywhere.

00:59:18.857 --> 00:59:23.370
MATT: "Should we conclude that your actions were
beyond reason and the moral fiber of this council

00:59:23.370 --> 00:59:29.922
"before your return, we will have no choice to put
a bounty on your heads, should you not return. I

00:59:29.922 --> 00:59:36.649
"really, really do not wish to do this. Do not make
me do this."

00:59:36.649 --> 00:59:40.617
ORION: I stand up. "No need for threats, friend.
Are we done here?"

00:59:40.617 --> 00:59:48.101
MATT: "I want to believe you all. I ask you, show
that my trust has not been misplaced all this

00:59:48.101 --> 00:59:51.723
"time. Now, you may leave."

00:59:51.723 --> 00:59:56.294
SAM: I look forward to the second parade you'll
throw for us after our names are cleared.

00:59:56.294 --> 00:59:58.993
MATT: "Very well."

00:59:58.993 --> 01:00:05.513
TRAVIS: I turn to the guards that were grabbing at
their weapons and I flex real fast at them and

01:00:05.513 --> 01:00:06.502
then I walk.

01:00:06.502 --> 01:00:08.083
MATT: Four of them go, (yelps).

01:00:08.083 --> 01:00:09.034
TRAVIS: Bitch!

01:00:09.034 --> 01:00:12.104
(laughter)

01:00:12.104 --> 01:00:19.502
MATT: As you guys go back out the doors that you
entered, the guards now a little closely following

01:00:19.502 --> 01:00:26.021
as you exit, leading you out of the palace, down
the front steps, and essentially stand at the

01:00:26.021 --> 01:00:27.634
front of the palace gates.

01:00:27.634 --> 01:00:32.683
LIAM: I'm sorry. I was just talking to one of your
friends. Have you seen a belt that is shaped like

01:00:32.683 --> 01:00:37.669
a snake? Sometimes it moves around on its own. And
it answers to the name Simon, but usually it's

01:00:37.669 --> 01:00:43.071
just a belt and looks really cool. Have you seen
it? Is there a lost and found I can check out?

01:00:43.071 --> 01:00:44.813
It's very dear to me.

01:00:44.813 --> 01:00:49.819
MATT: The guard just looks for a second and goes,
"I think you've got more important matters to deal

01:00:49.819 --> 01:00:52.466
"with before you go looking for a belt, sir."

01:00:52.466 --> 01:00:57.658
LIAM: Where's that other guy? He was more
receptive to this. Do I see that other guy?

01:00:57.658 --> 01:01:00.751
LAURA: Darling. Seriously.

01:01:00.751 --> 01:01:04.022
MATT: The guards all turn around and start
ascending the stairs.

01:01:04.022 --> 01:01:08.159
LIAM: It's on all the fan art. It really makes
sense to have it on me.

01:01:08.159 --> 01:01:10.516
MATT: They don't appear to be listening.

01:01:10.516 --> 01:01:16.918
LIAM: Keep an eye out for it. 100 gold to any chap
who finds it and holds onto it for me.

01:01:16.918 --> 01:01:22.219
MATT: Two of them stop in their step for a second
and then keep walking.

01:01:22.219 --> 01:01:23.604
LIAM: I'm a nice guy!

01:01:23.604 --> 01:01:25.501
(laughter)

01:01:25.501 --> 01:01:27.204
MATT: Go ahead and make a persuasion roll.

01:01:27.204 --> 01:01:29.387
TRAVIS: You're going to get six belts thrown at
you.

01:01:29.387 --> 01:01:31.118
LIAM: That's terrible. Six.

01:01:31.118 --> 01:01:36.530
MATT: It was a brief pause. But also. A brief
pause.

01:01:36.530 --> 01:01:40.615
LAURA: You have a two in persuasion? Oh wow.

01:01:40.615 --> 01:01:44.383
SAM: We'll break in tonight and find it.

01:01:44.383 --> 01:01:46.329
TRAVIS: Could we wait outside for Allura?

01:01:46.329 --> 01:01:48.161
LIAM: I'll risk it all.

01:01:48.161 --> 01:01:56.104
MATT: All right. So you are now currently there in
the cobblestone street of the Cloudtop District,

01:01:56.104 --> 01:02:02.052
removed from the Council of Tal'Dorei and left in
this interesting circumstance.

01:02:02.052 --> 01:02:04.469
SAM: Keyleth, what happened? Your magic didn't
work?

01:02:04.469 --> 01:02:06.189
MARISHA: No, it worked.

01:02:06.189 --> 01:02:07.490
LAURA: What happened?

01:02:07.490 --> 01:02:10.395
SAM: But Asum lied.

01:02:10.395 --> 01:02:12.328
ORION: He gave her a magic winky face.

01:02:12.328 --> 01:02:14.811
MARISHA: Yeah, essentially. Yeah. He gave me like
a--

01:02:14.811 --> 01:02:20.697
LAURA: What does that mean? Does that mean Uriel's
under their control? I don't understand.

01:02:20.697 --> 01:02:22.978
LIAM: Is he playing some sort of long game here?

01:02:22.978 --> 01:02:28.272
SAM: It must mean that we have something to fear
from Uriel. Or someone else close.

01:02:28.272 --> 01:02:32.493
MARISHA: I don't know who to trust anymore, to be
totally honest.

01:02:32.493 --> 01:02:33.811
TRAVIS: Really?

01:02:33.811 --> 01:02:43.636
MARISHA: It worked. I could feel it break. It
worked, and he's got some sort of long game. I

01:02:43.636 --> 01:02:49.560
don't know if it's because he doesn't want Uriel
to know, for whatever reason. I don't know if it's

01:02:49.560 --> 01:02:52.178
because he has some deeper, ulterior motive.

01:02:52.178 --> 01:02:55.467
LAURA: Do you think he was faking that he was
healed, and maybe he wasn't?

01:02:55.467 --> 01:02:58.599
TRAVIS: Or maybe we have to bring proof of their
vampirism back?

01:02:58.599 --> 01:02:59.627
MARISHA: No.

01:02:59.627 --> 01:03:00.969
TRAVIS: Oh.

01:03:00.969 --> 01:03:07.577
MARISHA: Wait. No to Vex. What was your question?

01:03:07.577 --> 01:03:10.812
TRAVIS: To bring back proof of them being
vampires.

01:03:10.812 --> 01:03:17.686
SAM: Proof would help. Hey! Don't we have a
prisoner? Can't we question the prisoner?

01:03:17.686 --> 01:03:20.738
LAURA: Is he bleeding out? What if he's dead?
We're so screwed!

01:03:20.738 --> 01:03:22.673
MARISHA: I made sure.

01:03:22.673 --> 01:03:27.119
LAURA: Yeah, the guy that Percy shot the hand off
of.

01:03:27.119 --> 01:03:29.173
MARISHA: I cauterized his wounds, remember?

01:03:29.173 --> 01:03:31.541
SAM: We should question him. He could have proof.

01:03:31.541 --> 01:03:35.457
LAURA: Oh shit! I hope everything's okay.

01:03:35.457 --> 01:03:47.702
ORION: Wait a minute! I really need to go to
Allura. She's our best interest right now.

01:03:47.702 --> 01:03:51.521
SAM: We get it! You want her body. Now's not the
time.

01:03:51.521 --> 01:03:55.894
ORION: It is beyond that. There are several
reasons to go. We need to get the Earring of

01:03:55.894 --> 01:04:05.698
Telescription. I need her to enchant something for
me, too. As well as the fact I fear that our keep

01:04:05.698 --> 01:04:10.033
may be in danger. I would like to ask her if she
may be able to set up a warding spell for--

01:04:10.033 --> 01:04:16.328
LAURA: Can you go get her and bring her to the
keep? I need to find out if this boy is all

01:04:16.328 --> 01:04:17.339
right.

01:04:17.339 --> 01:04:20.320
MARISHA: Well, we can split up. I can go with
you.

01:04:20.320 --> 01:04:27.014
MATT: As you guys are having this discussion, the
palace doors open and you hear the quick footsteps

01:04:27.014 --> 01:04:30.975
of Allura, rushing from the palace now, running
towards you guys.

01:04:30.975 --> 01:04:33.044
LAURA: Saving the day. Again.

01:04:33.044 --> 01:04:35.052
MARISHA: Wait, she's coming out of the palace?

01:04:35.052 --> 01:04:37.547
MATT: She's coming out of the palace, behind you
guys. Like after the council had just closed. The

01:04:37.547 --> 01:04:41.852
meeting had finished. She basically gave chase to
you guys and is now catching up to you on the

01:04:41.852 --> 01:04:42.711
street.

01:04:42.711 --> 01:04:44.793
SAM: What the shit happened in there?

01:04:44.793 --> 01:04:46.929
MARISHA: We were just talking about you!

01:04:46.929 --> 01:05:01.525
MATT: "Everyone-- I don't fully know what happened
last night, and--" She looks to you, Tiberius, and

01:05:01.525 --> 01:05:07.775
says, "You didn't, did you? Please tell me you did
not kill that woman."

01:05:07.775 --> 01:05:09.295
ORION: Oh, I absolutely did!

01:05:09.295 --> 01:05:12.356
LAURA: But she was attacking us.

01:05:12.356 --> 01:05:15.305
SAM: It looks bad, but she was a threat.

01:05:15.305 --> 01:05:23.555
ORION: Her and another one with this-- what was
he, a tiefling? Named the Broker attacked us. And

01:05:23.555 --> 01:05:25.088
that's why I killed her.

01:05:25.088 --> 01:05:35.019
MATT: "Brom's divination is very clear. And he
divined that the woman was currently filled with

01:05:35.019 --> 01:05:40.956
"fear, attempting to flee, and unconscious when she
was murdered."

01:05:40.956 --> 01:05:43.652
LIAM: How did she flee when she was unconscious?

01:05:43.652 --> 01:05:47.522
TRAVIS: She fled, went unconscious, then we
butchered her.

01:05:47.522 --> 01:05:51.495
MARISHA: Just accept it for what it is, guys.

01:05:51.495 --> 01:05:59.001
MATT: "I just worry. I know not what happened
here, and I heard what you said, and I honestly do

01:05:59.001 --> 01:06:05.271
"not trust the Briarwoods myself either. There was
something about that meal and the conversation,

01:06:05.271 --> 01:06:10.280
"and their presence that put me off entirely. It
was strange. And what you say makes a lot of

01:06:10.280 --> 01:06:20.566
"sense. Vampirism is a bit beyond what I was
expecting. I did sense some powerful masqueraded

01:06:20.566 --> 01:06:32.440
"arcane essence from Lady Briarwood. Look, I would
recommend for this to do your best to be thorough

01:06:32.440 --> 01:06:37.781
"in this. Bring back any and all information you
can. From the words I hear, you probably have at

01:06:37.781 --> 01:06:44.173
"best a few weeks before this comes to a close. And
if you don't have enough evidence to support your

01:06:44.173 --> 01:06:48.399
"argument-- well, I don't know."

01:06:48.399 --> 01:06:54.979
LIAM: Allura, all I know how to do is break locks,
but I've seen these people do things with magic

01:06:54.979 --> 01:07:01.390
that have defied expectations. Why can no one look
into my memory? You have looked across miles.

01:07:01.390 --> 01:07:04.751
Cannot anyone look into my mind and see?

01:07:04.751 --> 01:07:06.918
LAURA: They're going to do it!

01:07:06.918 --> 01:07:10.988
SAM: Yes, but that might not be proof enough for
them. Someone could have corrupted your mind.

01:07:10.988 --> 01:07:16.471
MATT: "You have to understand. Not all arcane
works that way. There are magics that can dabble

01:07:16.471 --> 01:07:21.148
"in that realm, but none that specialize that here
in Emon. Divination, yes there are elements of

01:07:21.148 --> 01:07:29.505
"that. We can see the physical. We can see certain
events. But to look into one's mind is a different

01:07:29.505 --> 01:07:30.877
"magic entirely."

01:07:30.877 --> 01:07:34.350
LIAM: Are there no spells that can divine if
someone's speaking true?

01:07:34.350 --> 01:07:41.537
MATT: "That was attempted during that council, but
after you left, Brom notified Uriel and the

01:07:41.537 --> 01:07:49.114
"Council that many of you were resistant to the
spell, and as such, it could not be verified."

01:07:49.114 --> 01:08:01.236
LAURA: (laughs) We should have rolled low! Just
tell us you're doing it, we won't resist it! What

01:08:01.236 --> 01:08:03.459
the shit? Doesn't even trust us to tell the
truth.

01:08:03.459 --> 01:08:05.613
TRAVIS: If we came back with proof?

01:08:05.613 --> 01:08:08.931
SAM: What sort of proof do you think they would
accept? The head of Lady Briarwood?

01:08:08.931 --> 01:08:12.875
LAURA: No, because it'll disappear the minute we
kill her or something. They're vampires, I don't

01:08:12.875 --> 01:08:14.349
know what they do.

01:08:14.349 --> 01:08:19.923
MATT: She gives a thought to that. She goes,
"Interestingly enough, if an artifact or an item

01:08:19.923 --> 01:08:24.714
"brought forth from them could be divined, that
should tell all."

01:08:24.714 --> 01:08:28.964
MARISHA: Is there still the remaining wreckage of
their carriage? Is that still there?

01:08:28.964 --> 01:08:33.161
MATT: "The carriage has been disposed. It's been
picked over, and there were remnants within the

01:08:33.161 --> 01:08:40.766
"rubble of some sort of a 'siggle' of teleportation.
But that is no-- a sigil, if you will."

01:08:40.766 --> 01:08:44.406
(laughter)

01:08:44.406 --> 01:08:47.900
TRAVIS: What sort of artifact? Like, a brooch? A
handbag?

01:08:47.900 --> 01:08:50.219
LIAM: Are we talking about that motherfucker's
teeth?

01:08:50.219 --> 01:08:51.513
ORION: I need to see that sigil.

01:08:51.513 --> 01:09:02.154
MATT: "Sigil. We're all learning together. That, I
believe, has all been investigated and kept under

01:09:02.154 --> 01:09:10.914
"lock and key with Asum. You would have to speak
with him. I would like to help. I cannot come with

01:09:10.914 --> 01:09:19.288
"you. I'm working on something else at the moment.
Ah!" And she reaches into her pocket and brings

01:09:19.288 --> 01:09:24.600
out your Earring of Transcription.

01:09:24.600 --> 01:09:27.187
ORION: Thank you so much, Lady Allura!

01:09:27.187 --> 01:09:34.637
MATT: As she hands it to you, she gives you a
really, really concerned look. And just gives it

01:09:34.637 --> 01:09:43.720
to you and hands it back. And it's a look of-- and
it hits you: it's a look of disappointment with a

01:09:43.720 --> 01:09:45.133
hint of heartbreak.

01:09:45.133 --> 01:09:48.715
TRAVIS: Oh, that's the worst! I'm not angry, I'm
just disappointed. Ugh!

01:09:48.715 --> 01:09:50.722
LIAM: I feel like I've failed you.

01:09:50.722 --> 01:09:51.977
TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:09:51.977 --> 01:09:58.174
MATT: She looks back to you as you take it and
goes, "Do your best to clear your name."

01:09:58.174 --> 01:09:59.718
ORION: I shall.

01:09:59.718 --> 01:10:03.947
MATT: "I know you come of noble blood, and many of
you stand to inspire many others of noble blood.

01:10:03.947 --> 01:10:10.291
"As celebrated heroes of this city, there is a lot
more on the line here besides just your

