01:25:14.039 --> 01:25:18.019
MATT: He does his finger like this and the gates
open in towards the inside of the keep wall.

01:25:18.019 --> 01:25:21.057
MARISHA: And what is wrong with you all today?!

01:25:21.057 --> 01:25:26.221
SAM: We had a really bad dinner last
night. That's all.

01:25:26.221 --> 01:25:28.073
LAURA: I head straight to the jail.

01:25:28.073 --> 01:25:30.333
MARISHA: I follow.

01:25:30.333 --> 01:25:33.209
MATT: As you guys are doing that, Tiberius, what's
the first thing you're trying to do?

01:25:33.209 --> 01:25:35.536
ORION: Stop by and pick up the decanter from the
temple.

01:25:35.536 --> 01:25:41.013
MATT: Okay. He said it required two days. It's
been less than a day since you dropped it off,

01:25:41.013 --> 01:25:42.715
just so you're aware.

01:25:42.715 --> 01:25:49.188
ORION: Then the only thing I do is visit the keep
with the sigils library or whatever.

01:25:49.188 --> 01:25:51.855
MATT: Oh, the Lyceum? Okay.

01:25:51.855 --> 01:25:55.561
LIAM: I'm not going. I'm just going to go hang out
up on the wall outside the keep.

01:25:55.561 --> 01:26:00.027
MATT: All right. As you head to the Lyceum, the
clerk lets you in. What are you specifically

01:26:00.027 --> 01:26:02.839
looking to find or research?

01:26:02.839 --> 01:26:07.687
ORION: The sigil that's closest to the Feywild.

01:26:07.687 --> 01:26:14.558
MATT: Okay. In researching what they have at their
disposal, you understand that the Feywild itself,

01:26:14.558 --> 01:26:21.261
because it is a separate plane, the magics to
traverse it are a little more difficult to do. If

01:26:21.261 --> 01:26:30.140
you notice-- and I'll confirm here just to be sure
that we're on the same page-- before I go full on

01:26:30.140 --> 01:26:39.197
this here. Pardon me, just a moment while I scan
through the book. The mighty book. The book of

01:26:39.197 --> 01:26:49.009
might. Yes. Sigils of teleportation require the
same plane of existence, meaning you can teleport

01:26:49.009 --> 01:26:54.559
anywhere within the Prime Material Plane that you
exist in. To traverse into the Feywild, you have

01:26:54.559 --> 01:26:59.339
to actually find a door into the Feywild, and then
you would be able to use a sigil from the

01:26:59.339 --> 01:27:00.683
Feywild.

01:27:00.683 --> 01:27:02.636
ORION: Then I only pick up my decanter.

01:27:02.636 --> 01:27:04.629
MATT: Which is not ready yet.

01:27:04.629 --> 01:27:08.786
ORION: I don't do that! Damn, I forgot! My
short-term memory is just jacked!

01:27:08.786 --> 01:27:10.728
MATT: It's all good. It's all good.

01:27:10.728 --> 01:27:12.950
TRAVIS: You know, somebody's been to the Feywild.

01:27:12.950 --> 01:27:19.450
MATT: Yeah. The Feywild. What you do find is that
the Feywild-- the boundaries between this realm

01:27:19.450 --> 01:27:28.451
and the Feywild tend to grow weaker at full moons.
It's tied to the moon cycle. And at certain

01:27:28.451 --> 01:27:36.551
places where nature is set to run wild. A lot of
druidic tribes tend to mark these locations, and

01:27:36.551 --> 01:27:39.057
in some cases actually guard them.

01:27:39.057 --> 01:27:44.524
LAURA: We know where a hole in one is. Grog went
through it.

01:27:44.524 --> 01:27:52.360
MATT: And if you recall-- good memory-- in the
Frostweald, the partially frozen forest where you

01:27:52.360 --> 01:27:59.950
had that conversation with the nymph-- that portal
that she existed through was specifically a door

01:27:59.950 --> 01:28:01.809
into the Feywild, which you recognized.

01:28:01.809 --> 01:28:03.204
ORION: What city was that near?

01:28:03.204 --> 01:28:04.796
MATT: That was south of Westruun.

01:28:04.796 --> 01:28:08.164
ORION: Then I'll go to the thing and I'll find the
Westruun sigil.

01:28:08.164 --> 01:28:16.623
MATT: Okay. Through your research, you do find a
sigil to Westruun. This is allowing you to go into

01:28:16.623 --> 01:28:24.089
this portion for this sigil because you've already
used the favor that you had to get the sigil of

01:28:24.089 --> 01:28:25.304
Kraghammer.

01:28:25.304 --> 01:28:29.609
ORION: No, I didn't. I used the amulet and we got
permission to come there. I saved that favor for

01:28:29.609 --> 01:28:30.552
this.

01:28:30.552 --> 01:28:33.426
MATT: Right, the favor for Gilmore. All I'm saying
is, you've used one of two favors to get that

01:28:33.426 --> 01:28:40.494
sigil. You have to invoke Gilmore's favor to get
this one. Okay. And since you're a part of the

01:28:40.494 --> 01:28:46.249
circumstance, you acquire the secondary sigil. You
now know, in your memory permanently, a sigil to

01:28:46.249 --> 01:28:49.757
Westruun. You don't know where in Westruun, but
you are connected there. If you choose to teleport

01:28:49.757 --> 01:29:02.244
there, you know how to. That favor has now been
used by Gilmore, so you can mark that. And on that

01:29:02.244 --> 01:29:06.871
note, we're going to go ahead and take a five
minute rest break. So yeah, restroom, snacks,

01:29:06.871 --> 01:29:10.926
drinks and we'll be back here in about five or so
minutes. We'll see you guys and continue this

01:29:10.926 --> 01:29:12.757
tense adventure.

01:29:12.757 --> 01:44:42.062
[break]

01:44:42.062 --> 01:44:46.705
MATT: Welcome back. We've had our break; we've
returned to the table. A quick note, we are 50

01:44:46.705 --> 01:44:48.670
subscribers away from our next giveaway.

01:44:48.670 --> 01:44:50.504
TRAVIS: 50? Come on!

01:44:50.504 --> 01:44:54.050
MATT: If we can get there, that'd be awesome!
We'll have our giveaway-- the signed cast Critical

01:44:54.089 --> 01:44:58.074
Role photo and the cast signed art poster by Kit
Buss.

01:44:58.074 --> 01:45:00.438
SAM: Kit Buss, ladies and gentlemen!

01:45:00.438 --> 01:45:10.955
MATT: Yeah! So you have all returned to the keep.
You have found yourselves down to the basement

01:45:10.955 --> 01:45:19.635
area. You hear the distant pinging of metal, an
occasional squeaking metallic noise. Like

01:45:19.635 --> 01:45:25.040
something is being altered, turned, or quenched in
a water trough. Like the process of

01:45:25.040 --> 01:45:26.516
blacksmithing.

01:45:26.516 --> 01:45:29.771
MARISHA: I go to the edge of the door and knock.

01:45:29.771 --> 01:45:39.117
MATT: As you knock on the metal door, it's like a
(boom). The pinging stops. Just hangs for a

01:45:39.117 --> 01:45:40.301
second.

01:45:40.301 --> 01:45:43.599
MARISHA: Percy? It's Keyleth.

01:45:43.599 --> 01:45:54.637
MATT: "Not right now. Please. I'm sorry. I just
need to clear my head."

01:45:54.637 --> 01:46:00.501
MARISHA: Okay. We'll be here.

01:46:00.501 --> 01:46:07.743
MATT: A moment later, you see Percy's eyes appear
at the edge of the door.

01:46:07.743 --> 01:46:09.722
MARISHA: Hi!

01:46:09.722 --> 01:46:18.152
MATT: Just looking at them, you can see they look
a little sunken, a little weary.

01:46:18.152 --> 01:46:20.145
MARISHA: Did you sleep?

01:46:20.145 --> 01:46:22.554
MATT: "Not as much as I'd like."

01:46:22.554 --> 01:46:24.619
MARISHA: Do you need anything?

01:46:24.619 --> 01:46:31.062
MATT: His eyes look away for a second, looks back
at you. "I'm all right. Thank you."

01:46:31.062 --> 01:46:38.419
MARISHA: We went and saw Uriel. Everyone in the
city hates us. They think we're all criminals.

01:46:38.419 --> 01:46:42.557
MATT: "Great. I have to get back to my work."

01:46:42.557 --> 01:46:44.256
MARISHA: Okay, yeah.

01:46:44.256 --> 01:46:48.318
MATT: The slit shuts.

01:46:48.318 --> 01:46:51.819
MARISHA: Oh, we'll see you later, then.

01:46:51.819 --> 01:47:01.132
MATT: You guys, however, walk down to the other
side of the cell. The cell door's been closed. The

01:47:01.132 --> 01:47:05.870
keys are hanging on the nail by it. You have not
used the cell until this point. It's technically

01:47:05.870 --> 01:47:10.674
pristine and unused since the construction of the keep,
but the keys still hang on the key ring. On the

01:47:10.674 --> 01:47:15.981
inside of it, there is no thatch. Nothing has been
put in to really make a comfortable floor. And

01:47:15.981 --> 01:47:18.252
hanging from manacles--

01:47:18.252 --> 01:47:19.983
LAURA: He's hanging?!

01:47:19.983 --> 01:47:21.536
SAM: We're the worst.

01:47:21.536 --> 01:47:24.443
MATT: He was put in as a prisoner.

01:47:24.443 --> 01:47:30.307
LAURA: I go and get the keys, and I take him down
from the manacles.

01:47:30.307 --> 01:47:37.478
MATT: As she rushes into the cell, begins
unlocking the manacles. He's unconscious at this

01:47:37.478 --> 01:47:42.261
time. Dirt streaked on his face and spatters of
dried blood from the blast of the gun.

01:47:42.261 --> 01:47:48.971
MARISHA: I go ahead and I administer Cure Wounds.

01:47:48.971 --> 01:47:59.279
MATT: The wound at this point has been cauterized.
You cast Cure Wounds as he starts to come to

01:47:59.279 --> 01:48:08.714
consciousness, in a heap on the ground. (coughs)
It appears he may be healed of any damage he may

01:48:08.714 --> 01:48:13.661
still be sustaining from that, but the fingers are
gone. This is beyond the magic you're capable of.

01:48:13.661 --> 01:48:23.551
He comes to consciousness on the ground, dirtied,
sore. Essentially broken before you.

01:48:23.551 --> 01:48:26.562
LAURA: Does he look like he's been bitten at all?

01:48:26.562 --> 01:48:27.970
MATT: You want to inspect?

01:48:27.970 --> 01:48:29.462
LAURA: Can I look at his neck?

01:48:29.462 --> 01:48:33.591
MATT: Go ahead and make an investigation check.

01:48:33.591 --> 01:48:36.397
LAURA: 20.

01:48:36.397 --> 01:48:42.063
MATT: Okay. You don't have a whole lot of
medicinal experience, but you take a moment and

01:48:42.063 --> 01:48:46.759
inspect both sides of his neck, tilting his head
side-to-side, as he's groaning and coming to.

01:48:46.759 --> 01:48:54.568
"What's going on?" Looking at the sides of his
neck, there does not appear to be any sign of any

01:48:54.568 --> 01:49:00.296
puncture wounds, anything that would be reminiscent 
of what your brother currently is healing from.

01:49:00.397 --> 01:49:04.136
MARISHA: Can I do an insight check to see if he is
also under a mind-control spell?

01:49:04.136 --> 01:49:10.174
MATT: At the moment, no. He is barely coming to
consciousness. There isn't enough of a presence at

01:49:10.174 --> 01:49:12.364
the moment to really read past.

01:49:12.364 --> 01:49:18.296
LAURA: Hey, there. Welcome back.

01:49:18.296 --> 01:49:20.896
MATT: "Where am I?"

01:49:20.896 --> 01:49:25.240
LAURA: You are being held, at the moment, for your
own safety.

01:49:25.240 --> 01:49:29.326
MATT: "For my own safety?"

01:49:29.326 --> 01:49:30.828
LAURA: Yeah.

01:49:30.828 --> 01:49:33.800
MATT: "How?" He looks at his hand.

01:49:33.800 --> 01:49:40.002
LAURA: Well, you were captured. We're pretty sure
the Briarwoods are going to be pissed as hell that

01:49:40.002 --> 01:49:44.365
you let the carriage get hit. We're just trying to
protect you, really.

01:49:44.365 --> 01:49:48.327
MARISHA: Really?

01:49:48.327 --> 01:49:52.944
SAM: I mean, his friends all died, so.

01:49:52.944 --> 01:50:00.517
MARISHA: Do we not feel like terrible people
enough already?

01:50:00.517 --> 01:50:04.931
SAM: Let's not have this conversation in front of
the prisoner. What's your name, boy!

01:50:04.931 --> 01:50:15.397
MATT: "My name is Desmond. Desmond Otham. I am the
son of a messenger, a courier of the de Rolo

01:50:15.397 --> 01:50:16.376
"family."

01:50:16.376 --> 01:50:19.307
MARISHA: He's the son of a messenger! That's even
more ironic!

01:50:19.307 --> 01:50:21.360
LAURA: Keyleth, do you need to step outside?

01:50:21.360 --> 01:50:24.289
MARISHA: No, I'm good. Continue. Son of a
messenger.

01:50:24.289 --> 01:50:30.562
LAURA: Right now, everyone is at risk. The
Briarwoods are bad people, you can attest to this,

01:50:30.562 --> 01:50:31.596
yes?

01:50:31.596 --> 01:50:35.181
MATT: "Yes."

01:50:35.181 --> 01:50:39.421
LAURA: Yes. Can you tell us everything you know
about them?

01:50:39.421 --> 01:50:47.849
MATT: "It's not going to matter. They're going to
find me. No one's supposed to get away."

01:50:47.849 --> 01:50:50.034
LAURA: You did!

01:50:50.034 --> 01:50:55.076
TRAVIS: There's always a first time.

01:50:55.076 --> 01:51:09.653
MATT: "I don't even know where to begin." He
adjusts himself, sliding back, putting his back

01:51:09.653 --> 01:51:12.780
against the wall of the cell.

01:51:12.780 --> 01:51:17.312
TRAVIS: I reach into the Bag of Holding. I pull
out the little goblet, and I pour some ale

01:51:17.312 --> 01:51:27.362
into a cup, and I hand him a little bit of ale. No,
it's fine. I take a little sip.

01:51:27.362 --> 01:51:35.816
MATT: "Please don't take offense if I don't trust
a drink from strangers who've, well, to be honest,

01:51:35.816 --> 01:51:38.473
"put me in this position."

01:51:38.473 --> 01:51:41.128
TRAVIS: All right. I put it beside him.

01:51:41.128 --> 01:51:46.213
MATT: "What do you want to know?"

01:51:46.213 --> 01:51:49.336
LAURA: We want to know if the Briarwoods--

01:51:49.336 --> 01:51:51.432
SAM: Are vampires.

01:51:51.432 --> 01:51:55.157
LAURA: Pretty much. They're vampires, right? I
mean, they're vampires.

01:51:55.157 --> 01:52:07.109
MATT: "All I know from the stories I've heard.
Mothers would tell their kids not to wander out at

01:52:07.109 --> 01:52:16.230
"night because dark things crawl in the shadows.
From what I know of vampires, they're not supposed

01:52:16.230 --> 01:52:22.773
"to go out during the day, right? But I'm sure I've
seen Lady Briarwood walk in the sun many a time."

01:52:22.773 --> 01:52:26.229
MARISHA: Only Lady Briarwood?

01:52:26.229 --> 01:52:39.847
MATT: "As I recall, yes. Lord Briarwood doesn't
make too many public appearances."

01:52:39.847 --> 01:52:49.592
SAM: Have there been any strange goings-on in
their residence? Sounds you've heard? People

01:52:49.592 --> 01:52:53.160
disappearing? Boxes coming in or out?

01:52:53.160 --> 01:53:01.308
LAURA: I cast Cure Wounds on him. I know Cure
Wounds, bitches! Level up!

01:53:01.308 --> 01:53:03.900
ORION: Have I reached the keep yet?

01:53:03.900 --> 01:53:12.258
MATT: No, not yet. You're probably about an hour
away, at this point. From the time you've taken to

01:53:12.258 --> 01:53:18.023
research, find this, learn the sigil to Westruun,
and begin your trek back. Fortunately, you got

01:53:18.023 --> 01:53:24.951
what you wanted, but you're out of the picture for
a little bit. He flinches as you put your hand up,

01:53:24.951 --> 01:53:31.384
and as you touch him, he exhales. You get
to him just as he can react, briefly.

01:53:31.384 --> 01:53:36.902
LAURA: 11. Do I add anything to that?

01:53:37.095 --> 01:53:40.123
MATT: I believe you add your Wisdom modifier to
that.

01:53:40.123 --> 01:53:41.782
LAURA: 14.

01:53:41.782 --> 01:53:57.696
MATT: He goes, "Look, my father worked for the de
Rolo family before the Briarwoods came. My father

01:53:57.696 --> 01:54:05.521
"vanished the night of their fall. My mother was
taken in madness and lost to the night this past

01:54:05.521 --> 01:54:17.905
"year. I was left alone. However, I knew the roads
well between here and Whitestone and places

01:54:17.905 --> 01:54:28.279
"between, growing up, traveling with my father. So
I was made to be a coachman for the new nobles. I

01:54:28.279 --> 01:54:32.469
"was paid, albeit little, and I was left alone.

01:54:32.469 --> 01:54:41.052
"Now, when I say the new nobles, there were nobles
that lived in Whitestone and worked along with the

01:54:41.052 --> 01:54:48.088
"de Rolos, and they helped oversee parts of the
town, the business, and the people. They had been

01:54:48.088 --> 01:54:54.946
"there for many generations of their respective
families, all under the de Rolos' guidance. But

01:54:54.946 --> 01:54:57.998
"the night the castle fell, those nobles were
dragged out.

01:54:57.998 --> 01:55:06.603
"It's strange. I mean, after the brutality of that
first night, it took days before the people of

01:55:06.603 --> 01:55:14.273
"Whitestone knew what had happened. We saw the fires,
we heard the battles, but no word of the victors

01:55:14.273 --> 01:55:21.858
"until three days had passed. We were too scared to
approach. By then, the Briarwoods called a town

01:55:21.858 --> 01:55:34.211
"meeting. They explained their new rule over the
town. A number objected, which is expected. Many

01:55:34.211 --> 01:55:43.185
"strong-willed folk in Whitestone, those days. They
were subsequently shot down at arrow-point. The

01:55:43.185 --> 01:55:45.442
"rest were quiet.

01:55:45.442 --> 01:55:53.506
"They then dragged out the noble families and executed
them, gifting their property and titles to the

01:55:53.506 --> 01:55:59.200
"various cut-throats and mercenaries they had
hired, brought across the channel to help them

01:55:59.200 --> 01:56:05.672
"take the town. They're not just two people;
they've used a lot of money and influence from wherever

01:56:05.672 --> 01:56:15.931
"they came from and brought a whole slew of very
dastardly folk, who have since been given the

01:56:15.931 --> 01:56:21.819
"titles once held by the other nobles of
Whitestone, living in their homes, taking their

01:56:21.819 --> 01:56:28.093
"tithes and most of the profits made from the businesses
they've forced us to continue to run from within

01:56:28.093 --> 01:56:37.625
"the city. A number of families fled into the woods
the night after the executions, using the shadows

01:56:37.625 --> 01:56:48.236
"of a moonless evening to keep safe. They were all
found hanging from the Sun Tree the next morning.

01:56:48.236 --> 01:56:55.639
"They kept things going as they were, mostly:
farming, logging, manning the white marble mines.

01:56:55.639 --> 01:57:04.309
"Business went as usual, all filling the pockets of
the new nobles and the Briarwoods. We were given

01:57:04.309 --> 01:57:11.562
"food, kept our immediate property. As long as we
didn't attempt to leave, we were promised safety.

01:57:11.562 --> 01:57:21.973
"That lasted for a few years, until the nobles
grew bored. Twitchy. They began to abuse the

01:57:21.973 --> 01:57:32.676
"people of Whitestone: scare us for fun, brand,
cut, steal the children, leave them back,

01:57:32.676 --> 01:57:42.640
"destroyed. They treat us like animals. Folks went
missing. I was beaten so bad by my employer, Count

01:57:42.640 --> 01:57:53.331
"Tylieri. But Lord Briarwood noticed, one night he
was passing through the city. He saw wounds on my

01:57:53.331 --> 01:58:00.957
"back when he was meeting with Count Tylieri. When
he asked me in private how I got them, I couldn't

01:58:00.957 --> 01:58:11.260
"lie. Couldn't resist him. He has a way of drawing
the truth out of you. Now, he told me this

01:58:11.260 --> 01:58:17.420
"unrefined violence was boorish to him and his
wife. That was the last I ever saw of Lord

01:58:17.420 --> 01:58:19.690
"Tylieri.

01:58:19.690 --> 01:58:26.340
"Lord and Lady Briarwood took me in as their own
driver and showed me Tylieri hanging from that

01:58:26.340 --> 01:58:35.420
"same Sun Tree the next morning. I was thankful,
then. In a strange way, life had been so terrible

01:58:35.420 --> 01:58:48.114
"for so long, it was the first time I saw someone
reach out and save me. They took me in as their

01:58:48.114 --> 01:58:54.130
"driver after that. It was a better thing to be
away from the anger and the fists of the thugs.

01:58:54.130 --> 01:59:01.730
"But the more I got to know the Briarwoods, the
more nightmarish I realized they were.

01:59:01.730 --> 01:59:10.566
"Behind the walls of that castle was no longer a
grand fortress that we heard it was. Seeing it,

01:59:10.566 --> 01:59:21.621
"keeping watch and guard over our people. No, that
was a domain of perverse magics and sacrilege, it was. The

01:59:21.621 --> 01:59:32.714
"green fog drifting out from the ground where it
stood. The same servants still run the halls, but

01:59:32.714 --> 01:59:44.984
"they aren't living. They're walking vessels of
undeath, their flesh slowly tearing away. The

01:59:44.984 --> 01:59:55.216
"garden in back lies shriveled, a foul green mist
forever pouring out. They're excavating something

01:59:55.216 --> 02:00:01.521
"in the dungeon, plundering pieces. A lot of their
attention seems to be down there; I don't know

02:00:01.521 --> 02:00:16.101
"why. I dare not wander too far down. They bring up
old things. Ancient things. Relics, books, bones.

02:00:16.101 --> 02:00:27.462
"You live in that world long enough, you believe
there is no way out. Death would be easy, though

02:00:27.462 --> 02:00:32.902
"I've seen that death is no real end there. It's
just the beginning of a whole new terrible

02:00:32.902 --> 02:00:38.517
"existence. A far worse fate."

02:00:38.517 --> 02:00:52.304
LAURA: If we keep you here, protected, would you
be willing to tell your story to someone else?

02:00:52.304 --> 02:00:58.553
MATT: "Who would you want me to tell it to?"

02:00:58.553 --> 02:01:07.149
LAURA: The emperor. The guards here. An army that
could go and fight the Briarwoods.

02:01:07.149 --> 02:01:14.781
MATT: "Maybe."

02:01:14.781 --> 02:01:21.635
MARISHA: This could be an option to save
Whitestone, and you would have your freedom.

02:01:21.635 --> 02:01:26.855
MATT: "I don't know. You don't know what it's
like. You don't know what they've done. They're

02:01:26.855 --> 02:01:28.573
"going to find me."

02:01:28.573 --> 02:01:38.346
SAM: We can protect you. We are safe here in this
keep, and you're surrounded by very powerful

02:01:38.346 --> 02:01:40.172
allies now.

02:01:40.172 --> 02:01:43.241
TRAVIS: We've stood before them, and we did not
fall.

02:01:43.241 --> 02:01:45.411
LAURA: It's true.

02:01:45.411 --> 02:01:51.364
MATT: "I'll think about it."

02:01:51.364 --> 02:02:08.944
MARISHA: Would you like to stay in the guest room
upstairs? You'd be more comfortable. You could get

02:02:08.944 --> 02:02:10.242
a good night's rest.

02:02:10.242 --> 02:02:14.084
LAURA: Far more comfortable. A little less safe.
I'm going to put it out there.

02:02:14.084 --> 02:02:20.485
MATT: That resonates with him immediately, and his
eyes flash open. "I mean no disrespect, but if

02:02:20.485 --> 02:02:22.688
"this is safe, then I'd rather stay here."

02:02:22.688 --> 02:02:27.332
LAURA: I think it is. And we will bring a bed down
to you, make sure you're comfortable. I don't want

02:02:27.332 --> 02:02:29.157
you sleeping on the floor. That's terrible.

02:02:29.157 --> 02:02:31.893
MATT: "You're all being very accommodating."

02:02:31.893 --> 02:02:41.107
TRAVIS: You'll get every consideration for
protection. We value your info very much.

02:02:41.107 --> 02:02:46.763
MARISHA: You're also the key to our own freedom,
so it's important.

02:02:46.763 --> 02:02:51.940
SAM: You also caught us on a day where we're
trying to be nicer to people.

02:02:51.940 --> 02:02:56.599
(laughter)

02:02:56.599 --> 02:02:58.747
SAM: Lucky for you.

02:02:58.747 --> 02:03:01.492
LIAM: Just be glad you're not an old woman.

02:03:01.492 --> 02:03:06.531
MATT: "I'll stay here for now."

02:03:06.531 --> 02:03:08.945
LAURA: All right.

02:03:08.945 --> 02:03:16.578
MATT: "I need to think on it. I've been promised
such protection before."

02:03:16.578 --> 02:03:18.454
SAM: From the Briarwoods?

02:03:18.454 --> 02:03:25.554
MATT: "From a few. And they're dead. An enemy of
an enemy doesn't necessarily make them a friend,

02:03:25.554 --> 02:03:27.034
"I've discovered."

02:03:27.034 --> 02:03:37.813
MARISHA: No, but it can make them allies if they
have mutual enemies. Of their enemies. It's a

02:03:37.813 --> 02:03:39.285
little complicated.

02:03:39.285 --> 02:03:43.092
MATT: This whole conversation, the emotional
recalling of everything, you can see has been very

02:03:43.092 --> 02:03:50.422
taxing on him and his still mostly conscious
state. He looks exhausted, scared, and still

02:03:50.422 --> 02:03:53.400
trying to suss out all the information coming at
him right now.

02:03:53.400 --> 02:03:56.250
MARISHA: Grog, why don't you carry the bed down
from upstairs?

02:03:56.250 --> 02:04:02.120
TRAVIS: Not a problem. Keep the goblet nearby. It
is very nice ale.

02:04:02.120 --> 02:04:04.260
MARISHA: Would you like something to eat?

02:04:04.260 --> 02:04:06.557
MATT: "Yes, please."

02:04:06.557 --> 02:04:09.497
MARISHA: We'll have our staff bring down some
food.

02:04:09.497 --> 02:04:14.194
MATT: He takes the goblet. He looks at it, smells
it, but still holds it at bay as you walk off. You

02:04:14.194 --> 02:04:19.124
eventually go-- easy enough for you-- take the
bed. You have to turn it to the side to take it

02:04:19.124 --> 02:04:21.335
out, which causes all of the cushions to fall
out.

02:04:21.335 --> 02:04:22.634
TRAVIS: Aw, shit.

02:04:22.634 --> 02:04:24.418
(laughter)

02:04:24.418 --> 02:04:29.413
TRAVIS: I grab a little pillow with my toes, and I
hobble down.

02:04:29.413 --> 02:04:32.344
MATT: It takes about 20 minutes and three trips,
but you manage to get the bed down there from the

02:04:32.344 --> 02:04:33.380
guest room.

02:04:33.380 --> 02:04:35.311
TRAVIS: Not a problem.

02:04:35.311 --> 02:04:40.109
MATT: When you fit it in the cell-- and it's not a
large cell; it's maybe ten by ten feet maximum.

02:04:40.109 --> 02:04:54.079
You place it there. As you guys walk back, you
notice as you see Grog walking back down the

02:04:54.079 --> 02:04:58.967
stairway-- right around the corner as you go down
the steps, the hallway goes to the cell, and it

02:04:58.967 --> 02:05:03.608
turns to the right and to the left to the
workshop. You see around the corner a shoulder,

02:05:03.653 --> 02:05:10.504
listening in. There's a person. And you recognize
that it is Percy. Percy has stepped out of the

02:05:10.504 --> 02:05:14.634
workshop and apparently has been hearing
everything this entire time.

02:05:14.634 --> 02:05:17.654
LAURA: Are you all right?

02:05:17.654 --> 02:05:22.563
MATT: "I'm fine." And Percy immediately steps away
and you hear the door close with a slam.

02:05:22.563 --> 02:05:24.516
LAURA: Give him time.

02:05:24.516 --> 02:05:26.344
SAM: So moody!

02:05:26.344 --> 02:05:35.115
LAURA: So yeah, I'm going to lock it. I'm just
going to lock your door. To make sure you're safe,

02:05:35.115 --> 02:05:37.728
make sure nobody can get in.

02:05:37.728 --> 02:05:46.168
MATT: "Keep him away from me. Who is that?"

02:05:46.168 --> 02:05:53.286
SAM: He's a friend. I know it doesn't seem like it
from the condition of your paw, but he's a friend.

02:05:53.286 --> 02:05:59.077
He's in the same boat as you, trying to stay safe
from danger.

02:05:59.077 --> 02:06:03.565
LAURA: The Briarwoods destroyed his family, as
well.

02:06:03.565 --> 02:06:12.279
MATT: And you see now, there's like this look of
tension on his face that's mixed with tired. And

02:06:12.279 --> 02:06:16.354
eventually finding the bed and takes the goblet--
still filled, has not drunk from it-- just slips it

02:06:16.354 --> 02:06:19.052
next to the side of the bed. Eventually food is
brought down.

02:06:19.052 --> 02:06:21.595
LAURA: And a chamber pot, because come on!

02:06:21.595 --> 02:06:29.223
MATT: All the basic pleasantries are brought
within the cell. He lies on the bed and takes the

02:06:29.223 --> 02:06:32.815
plate up with him and starts just scarfing some of
the bread rolls down. And immediately starts going

02:06:32.815 --> 02:06:36.706
for the mashed potatoes. You can see a decent meal
hasn't been had in quite a while. Especially the

02:06:36.706 --> 02:06:40.582
journey, what is essentially a seven to eight day
journey from Whitestone, probably has not been

02:06:40.582 --> 02:06:47.757
very kind to him. Eats and then promptly passes
out on the bed. Food still mashed on the side of

02:06:47.757 --> 02:06:50.510
the face. Just goes straight into a slumber.

02:06:50.510 --> 02:06:55.728
TRAVIS: Is there any other entrance to the cell
area besides the door? No barred windows or

02:06:55.728 --> 02:06:57.000
anything like that?

02:06:57.000 --> 02:07:02.445
MATT: No. It's underground. It's all solid, solid
stone walls. And there is the barred front door,

02:07:02.445 --> 02:07:07.292
and then just goes right into the hallway that
goes up the stairs to your left and across the way

02:07:07.292 --> 02:07:08.990
and around the corner to the workshop.

02:07:08.990 --> 02:07:13.267
TRAVIS: You can't cast any kind of alarm system? A
trigger?

02:07:13.267 --> 02:07:15.872
LAURA: So that Percy can't get anything through
there?

02:07:15.872 --> 02:07:23.772
MARISHA: Let me reference my spell tome. It's not
a common one. It's situational. But let me check

02:07:23.772 --> 02:07:28.502
real quick. I haven't read that chapter from my
book in a while.

02:07:28.502 --> 02:07:33.760
ORION: Is Allura on the way back from the
Lyceum?

02:07:33.760 --> 02:07:43.672
MATT: No, the Lyceum is in the Erudite District.
Allura's tower is in the Cloudtop, which is the

02:07:43.672 --> 02:07:45.923
central part of Emon.

02:07:45.923 --> 02:07:51.447
LAURA: I do want to go check out that bird
creature at the farmhouse tonight.

02:07:51.447 --> 02:07:53.884
SAM: Yes. Well, have we stationed a guard down
there?

02:07:53.884 --> 02:07:57.518
TRAVIS: We should. We have five or six.

02:07:57.518 --> 02:08:01.774
SAM: All right. I'll go talk to Cordell. That's
his name, right?

02:08:01.774 --> 02:08:04.048
TRAVIS: No, not Cordell. Let's get somebody else.

02:08:04.048 --> 02:08:07.665
LAURA: Get the crossbow guy that we like so much.
The guy that's the captain of the guards.

02:08:07.665 --> 02:08:12.563
SAM: Is that Kendrick? Or Shayne? Oh, the girl?

02:08:12.563 --> 02:08:16.348
LAURA: No, the guy. He's awesome and he's an
archer, as well.

02:08:16.348 --> 02:08:17.250
SAM: Jarett?

02:08:17.250 --> 02:08:18.697
LAURA: Jarett. That's it!

02:08:18.697 --> 02:08:22.803
SAM: All right, we'll get Jarett. Oh, Jarett?

02:08:22.803 --> 02:08:26.403
MATT: You make your way to the back part of the
wall, and there is a small tower that's

02:08:26.403 --> 02:08:31.930
constructed as part of the back wall. That's where
Jarett usually keeps watch. Jarett has the

02:08:31.930 --> 02:08:36.538
in-between shift between the guards, so he can be
present for both sides and keep a watch during the

02:08:36.538 --> 02:08:43.826
afternoon until the nighttime. Probably till about
midnight or so. So as you make your way out of the

02:08:43.826 --> 02:08:49.844
keep, Tiberius, are you heading back to the keep
or are you heading toward the Cloudtop District?

02:08:49.844 --> 02:08:56.502
This will dictate whether or not you show up
around this time.

02:08:56.502 --> 02:08:59.618
ORION: I'm going to Allura's.

02:08:59.618 --> 02:09:04.120
LAURA: I'm staying down in the prison, just for
the time being. I don't want to leave him alone

02:09:04.120 --> 02:09:05.607
with Percy.

02:09:05.607 --> 02:09:11.862
MATT: You go to find Jarett, who's up at the top
of the tower. And as you call to him, Jarett leans

02:09:11.862 --> 02:09:23.000
over. And you see him, you know, short jet-black
hair, darker complexion. Very handsome, younger,

02:09:23.000 --> 02:09:28.368
early-twenties guy. Well-dressed over his studded
leather armor that he wears underneath and has the

02:09:28.368 --> 02:09:33.264
crossbow on the side. He leans over. "Scanlan, it
has been some time. It is so good to hear from

02:09:33.264 --> 02:09:36.404
"you. What can I be of service for?"

02:09:36.404 --> 02:09:41.470
SAM: We need you to watch a prisoner for us,
downstairs in our jail cell, which we had built

02:09:41.470 --> 02:09:49.333
and are now using. You'll be guarding the prisoner
to make sure he doesn't escape, but also making

02:09:49.333 --> 02:09:57.833
sure he stays safe. He possesses information
that's very valuable to us. And one of the people

02:09:57.833 --> 02:10:07.320
who hires you might try to kill him, so if Percy
tries to go in there, can you stop him without

02:10:07.320 --> 02:10:09.677
hurting either party?

02:10:09.677 --> 02:10:18.757
MATT: "I imagine this would be very well-suited
for my skill set. It will be strange to keep watch

02:10:18.757 --> 02:10:25.290
"against one of my employers, but he's been a bit
sheepish around me anyway."

02:10:25.290 --> 02:10:28.562
SAM: You think you could take Percy?

02:10:28.562 --> 02:10:31.384
MATT: "Well, I think I can at least talk some
sense into him!"

02:10:31.384 --> 02:10:32.703
TRAVIS: I like him!

02:10:32.703 --> 02:10:38.948
SAM: Wow! Jarett, you're ballsy! Just out of
curiosity, if he was running at you, what would

02:10:38.948 --> 02:10:39.890
you do?

02:10:39.890 --> 02:10:43.391
(laughter)

02:10:43.391 --> 02:10:48.225
MATT: "Well, first and foremost, I would dive in
the forward motion, leg out, to put him off

02:10:48.225 --> 02:10:53.398
"balance. This would be from a frontal melee--
you're messing with me, aren't you?"

02:10:53.398 --> 02:10:55.067
SAM: A little bit!

02:10:55.067 --> 02:10:59.662
MATT: "Ah, gnomes! Very well."

02:10:59.662 --> 02:11:02.475
SAM: Do you need anything to help?

02:11:02.475 --> 02:11:08.271
MATT: "I have access to my own private armory, and
I have utmost faith."

02:11:08.271 --> 02:11:14.489
SAM: All right. Well, keep him safe and there's an
extra five gold in it for you?

02:11:14.489 --> 02:11:15.965
LAURA: Oh! Pathetic!

02:11:15.965 --> 02:11:18.359
SAM: I don't know! Ten! Ten gold!

02:11:18.359 --> 02:11:19.683
MATT: "Gnomes."

02:11:19.683 --> 02:11:22.802
SAM: I don't know how money works. We'll talk to
Vex about it.

02:11:22.802 --> 02:11:27.619
MATT: "Certainly. All right. I will do this." And
he stands up, and goes and starts gathering his

02:11:27.619 --> 02:11:32.164
general setup supplies inside the guard tower. As
you walk back to the keep, you hear him whistle

02:11:32.164 --> 02:11:37.104
and start calling out to Shayne to go ahead and
take over, up in the tower.

02:11:37.104 --> 02:11:45.974
LIAM: I wasn't there for any of that. I was
upstairs on the roof, just thinking.

02:11:45.974 --> 02:11:56.917
MATT: Tiberius, you make your way into the
Cloudtop District. As you come to the front gates

02:11:56.917 --> 02:12:01.812
of the district, the guards that normally
recognize you and welcome you in, recognize you

02:12:01.812 --> 02:12:04.892
and stand firm, weapons at the ready.

02:12:04.892 --> 02:12:06.971
ORION: At Allura's tower?

02:12:06.971 --> 02:12:10.248
MATT: At the Cloudtop District entirely. You guys
had to get written permission to enter there when

02:12:10.248 --> 02:12:14.251
you first came to Emon, anyway, since that's where
the nobility and many of the important figures of

02:12:14.251 --> 02:12:19.456
Emon reside. It appears that since you've been
taken out of the Council and you're under

02:12:19.456 --> 02:12:25.930
investigation, your access to such a sensitive
location within Emon has been temporarily revoked,

02:12:25.930 --> 02:12:28.749
and the guards are not letting you through.

02:12:28.749 --> 02:12:34.682
ORION: Is that it? So I just turn around? Go
back?

02:12:34.682 --> 02:12:37.838
MATT: It's up to you. The guards are just there,
standing.

02:12:37.838 --> 02:12:49.348
ORION: Greeting and salutations. I'm Tiberius
Stormwind from Draconia. Moreover, a member of Vox

02:12:49.348 --> 02:12:58.394
Machina, over at Greyskull Keep. It seems that you
all are posturing and whatnot. (chuckles) It's

02:12:58.394 --> 02:13:04.442
adorable. But I'm here to see Lady Allura. Could
you let her know that I would like to speak to

02:13:04.442 --> 02:13:09.480
her, or get out of my way so I can just go over
there and tell her myself?

02:13:09.480 --> 02:13:13.432
MATT: "We have direct orders to not let you or any
other member of Vox Machina into the Cloudtop

02:13:13.432 --> 02:13:19.730
"District until your investigation is complete. So
no, and no."

02:13:19.730 --> 02:13:27.230
ORION: Well, do the second thing. If you don't do
one thing, do one of the other things.

02:13:27.230 --> 02:13:34.783
MATT: "Your information and wish has been
processed, taken into consideration. Thank you

02:13:34.783 --> 02:13:36.565
"very much. Please be on your way."

02:13:36.565 --> 02:13:44.578
ORION: Oh, it has been, it has been processed! Oh,
that's good to know! I appreciate that. Very well.

02:13:44.578 --> 02:13:47.487
I cast Fly on myself and I go back to the keep.

02:13:47.487 --> 02:14:04.873
MATT: Okay. (whoosh) They both did not expect that
exit. You essentially Superman-ed. You're just

02:14:04.873 --> 02:14:11.692
like (thud). Little cloud of smoke in the shape of
a dragonborn left behind. All right. So as you

02:14:11.692 --> 02:14:16.471
cruise over, you see in the distance, from where
you're standing at the top of the keep, you see a

02:14:16.471 --> 02:14:23.856
distant bead of dark shadow that approaches and
grows larger, and it is an air-cruising Tiberius

02:14:23.856 --> 02:14:26.929
making his way towards the keep.

02:14:26.929 --> 02:14:32.852
LIAM: I hide behind-- I don't want to get hit, so
I'm going to crouch down a little bit, carefully

02:14:32.852 --> 02:14:38.603
behind one of the pieces of wall. Yeah. Rough
landings, sometimes.

02:14:38.603 --> 02:14:41.833
ORION: I fly in. Vox Machina!

02:14:41.833 --> 02:14:45.191
LIAM: Easy. Be careful.

02:14:45.191 --> 02:14:48.905
ORION: Sorry. Hi. What are you doing? Are you up
here thinking?

02:14:48.905 --> 02:14:57.475
LIAM: Why, I suppose I was. The others are
downstairs interrogating that boy. Where have you

02:14:57.475 --> 02:14:58.913
been?

02:14:58.913 --> 02:15:06.011
ORION: Off doing things that wasn't really that
productive, overall, but they don't like me

02:15:06.011 --> 02:15:09.487
anywhere, especially now.

02:15:09.487 --> 02:15:12.799
LIAM: Do you want to have a drink?

02:15:12.799 --> 02:15:14.664
ORION: Yes, actually, I do.

02:15:14.664 --> 02:15:17.953
LIAM: I've got a flask. You normally drink water.
You want a shot, though?

02:15:17.953 --> 02:15:22.586
ORION: Yes, I would love some alcohol. This calls
for alcohol.

02:15:22.586 --> 02:15:29.451
LIAM: I pull out my flask, and I'm amazed, because
I've never seen this and I hand it over to him.

02:15:29.451 --> 02:15:32.649
ORION: Oh yes. (whoosh)

02:15:32.649 --> 02:15:35.644
SAM: Did you eat the flask?

02:15:35.644 --> 02:15:38.271
ORION: No, fire breath.

02:15:38.271 --> 02:15:42.865
LIAM: Do you want to pass that bad boy back? Is it
hot?

02:15:42.865 --> 02:15:44.592
MATT: It's empty.

02:15:44.592 --> 02:15:49.049
LIAM: Oh, it's empty! Well, I guess that was worth
it.

02:15:49.049 --> 02:15:53.188
ORION: (slurred) What? What are you talking about?
Don't you tell me how to drink. Oh, you!

02:15:53.188 --> 02:16:00.478
TRAVIS: I come out from the castle into the
courtyard, and I go, hey! I feel like chicken

02:16:00.478 --> 02:16:03.276
tonight! Can we go hunt this big bird?

02:16:03.276 --> 02:16:06.705
LIAM: Tiberius-- I just got him drunk!

02:16:06.705 --> 02:16:07.863
TRAVIS: Really?

02:16:07.863 --> 02:16:11.540
ORION: (slurred) He gave me a shot of his flask
water, and it's so good.

02:16:11.540 --> 02:16:14.602
TRAVIS: Are you sure you didn't hit him with the
blunt side of your knife again?

02:16:14.602 --> 02:16:18.558
LIAM: No, no, he took a shot of the old firewater,
and I don't know. We might want to slap him a

02:16:18.558 --> 02:16:19.655
bit--

02:16:19.655 --> 02:16:24.160
ORION: (slurred) Allura doesn't like me anymore
because I killed that bitch who tried to kill us,

02:16:24.160 --> 02:16:26.784
and now she's fucking-- nobody likes us!

02:16:26.784 --> 02:16:28.416
LIAM: Let's find Keyleth.

02:16:28.416 --> 02:16:32.602
TRAVIS: Yeah. Smart. Keyleth!

02:16:32.602 --> 02:16:36.521
MARISHA: What? I was reading. What?

02:16:36.521 --> 02:16:38.622
TRAVIS: Tibs got turnt up. Will you fix it?

02:16:38.622 --> 02:16:39.995
MARISHA: How?

02:16:39.995 --> 02:16:41.659
ORION: Vax gave me--

02:16:41.659 --> 02:16:44.237
MARISHA: What did you do? Why are you touching
me?

02:16:44.237 --> 02:16:47.397
ORION: Oh, I love protecting you, it is-- and
Lockheed is, he loves you, too--

02:16:47.397 --> 02:16:49.131
MARISHA: Don't touch me right now!

02:16:49.131 --> 02:16:52.174
ORION: See, I'm telling you, nobody likes me.

02:16:52.174 --> 02:16:56.636
LIAM: I gave him his first drinky. I'm sorry. Do
you think you could pull him out of it?

02:16:56.636 --> 02:16:58.044
MARISHA: What?

02:16:58.044 --> 02:17:01.961
LIAM: I thought he was going to say no! He didn't
leave me any.

02:17:01.961 --> 02:17:14.584
ORION: It's good. Hi. How are you? I'm Tiberius--
Draconia. You are princess pretty face. He likes

02:17:14.584 --> 02:17:16.583
you, too.

02:17:16.583 --> 02:17:23.180
LIAM: Vax walks away, off the roof. Out of here.
I'm gone!

02:17:23.180 --> 02:17:25.117
TRAVIS: Grog is riveted.

02:17:25.117 --> 02:17:29.479
ORION: Human kissy mouth, with you is-- (vomits)

02:17:29.479 --> 02:17:32.343
(laughter)

02:17:32.343 --> 02:17:36.117
ORION: I'm good.

02:17:36.117 --> 02:17:38.250
MARISHA: If you touch me one more time!

02:17:38.250 --> 02:17:40.617
ORION: Oh! Sorry. Did you need to go somewhere?

02:17:40.617 --> 02:17:47.244
MARISHA: I am doing something else, a request that
was already made previously, before "can we fix

02:17:47.244 --> 02:17:51.814
"drunk Tiberius," so I'm a little busy! Why don't
you go sleep it off, take a nap, and I will deal

02:17:51.814 --> 02:17:53.629
with you in a second.

02:17:53.629 --> 02:17:55.024
ORION: Is it sleepy time?

02:17:55.024 --> 02:17:56.127
MARISHA: For you.

02:17:56.127 --> 02:17:57.721
ORION: Should I cast Fireball?

02:17:57.721 --> 02:18:05.266
MARISHA: Oh my god. And I shove him into the cell
and put him in bed--

02:18:05.266 --> 02:18:08.575
TRAVIS: No, we're not in the prison. We're out in
the courtyard.

02:18:08.575 --> 02:18:12.184
MARISHA: Oh, I thought that you said-- everyone
was like, Keyleth!

02:18:12.184 --> 02:18:16.285
LAURA: I'm still in the prison. Everybody else is
out of the prison.

02:18:16.285 --> 02:18:19.366
MATT: So where do you push him?

02:18:19.366 --> 02:18:22.025
ORION: She pushed me off the roof.

02:18:22.025 --> 02:18:24.627
MARISHA: No! I thought we were downstairs.

02:18:24.627 --> 02:18:28.788
ORION: I fall off the roof. I still have Fly on
myself, don't I?

02:18:28.788 --> 02:18:34.862
MARISHA: You don't fall off the roof. I don't know
what I do with him. I let him pass out.

02:18:34.862 --> 02:18:38.005
ORION: I'm going to get a sandwich.

02:18:38.005 --> 02:18:40.499
MARISHA: I let him go get a sandwich.

02:18:40.499 --> 02:18:43.118
SAM: I encourage sandwich!

02:18:43.118 --> 02:18:47.211
(laughter)

02:18:47.211 --> 02:18:53.746
MATT: That's the quote of the night. Encouraged to
get a sandwich, Tiberius wanders off. What are you

02:18:53.746 --> 02:18:56.196
doing to prepare what you were doing?

02:18:56.196 --> 02:18:58.290
MARISHA: I don't know! I got distracted!

02:18:58.290 --> 02:18:59.563
ORION: I'm not there.

02:18:59.563 --> 02:19:00.692
MARISHA: Okay.

02:19:00.692 --> 02:19:04.326
MATT: Well, as the day progresses, what would you
guys like to do?

02:19:04.326 --> 02:19:12.953
MARISHA: Wait. My idea. Okay. We were wanting
extra fortification? We were wanting extra

02:19:12.953 --> 02:19:21.508
protection. Okay? I can't necessarily cast a big
spell. I could cast Hallucinatory Terrain. We have

02:19:21.508 --> 02:19:25.685
a few options; I'm giving them to you all. I can
cast Hallucinatory Terrain to make this look like

02:19:25.685 --> 02:19:30.552
something else. I don't think-- I don't know. I
don't know if that's a good idea. I don't know. I

02:19:30.552 --> 02:19:38.965
could conjure a few woodland beings for, like, extra
bears. We could have some bears guarding the

02:19:38.965 --> 02:19:47.842
palace. I could also throw up a Wall of Thorns, to
barrier the cell with the wall of thorns. You're

02:19:47.842 --> 02:19:49.488
not here?

02:19:49.488 --> 02:19:53.496
SAM: I think everyone left. I think it's just you
and me up here, and drunk Tiberius.

02:19:53.496 --> 02:19:59.956
MARISHA: I went downstairs, and I'm saying this to
the group so I don't have to repeat myself!

02:19:59.956 --> 02:20:04.371
ORION: Oh, so then I turn around with my sandwich
and am like, we have to just make Allura talk to

02:20:04.371 --> 02:20:06.289
us. She can fix everything.

02:20:06.289 --> 02:20:13.015
TRAVIS: I grab Tiberius's mouth and I cover it.
Please continue.

02:20:13.015 --> 02:20:14.742
SAM: Wall of Thorns could be good.

02:20:14.742 --> 02:20:16.662
LAURA: I like Wall of Thorns.

02:20:16.662 --> 02:20:22.738
MARISHA: The thing with Wall of Thorns is it's not
super big. It's 60 feet.

02:20:22.738 --> 02:20:24.020
SAM: That's pretty big!

02:20:24.020 --> 02:20:25.744
LAURA: Oh. That's not the whole place, though.

02:20:25.744 --> 02:20:29.707
SAM: Oh, 60 feet long. I thought you meant high.

02:20:29.707 --> 02:20:34.468
MARISHA: No, it's 100 feet high. It's really high.
Actually, I don't know how high it is. Don't quote

02:20:34.468 --> 02:20:41.227
me on that. But it's not that long, but we could
fortify the doors more. Have bears. We could do

02:20:41.227 --> 02:20:43.086
multiple things, too.

02:20:43.086 --> 02:20:48.874
LIAM: I think that the Hallucinatory Terrain
wouldn't work. I felt like they could see right

02:20:48.874 --> 02:20:50.224
through me.

02:20:50.224 --> 02:20:51.530
TRAVIS: I think so, too.

02:20:51.530 --> 02:20:52.756
MARISHA: On the Briarwoods?

02:20:52.756 --> 02:20:54.835
LAURA: Yeah, they can see through illusions pretty
darn well.

02:20:54.835 --> 02:20:57.356
SAM: Listen, Percy's here. He can defend for us.

02:20:57.356 --> 02:20:59.265
ORION: No, you need a warding spell.

02:20:59.265 --> 02:21:02.869
SAM: Why don't we just leave someone behind?

02:21:02.869 --> 02:21:05.392
MARISHA: Percy's behind.

02:21:05.392 --> 02:21:11.065
TRAVIS: Percy's here and so are five? Six? How
many employees do we have?

02:21:11.065 --> 02:21:13.329
LAURA: Our very capable guards.

02:21:13.329 --> 02:21:17.800
TRAVIS: Why don't you make some extra bears that
don't hate us?

02:21:17.800 --> 02:21:19.325
MARISHA: Huh?

02:21:19.325 --> 02:21:21.768
TRAVIS: Why don't you make some extra bears that
don't hate us?

02:21:21.768 --> 02:21:23.518
MARISHA: All right, I'll make some extra bears.

02:21:23.518 --> 02:21:25.971
ORION: Put some little hats on them and make them
cute.

02:21:25.971 --> 02:21:30.065
LIAM: Do you think you could fix him? Because he's
a lot of firepower if we're going to go--

02:21:30.065 --> 02:21:34.715
MARISHA: What gets rid of drunkenness? (laughs)

02:21:34.715 --> 02:21:36.056
LAURA: Maybe Restoration?

02:21:36.056 --> 02:21:37.634
MATT: Restoration would probably take care of it.

02:21:37.634 --> 02:21:40.423
MARISHA: I don't want to burn a Restoration spell
on your drunkenness.

02:21:40.423 --> 02:21:42.835
LAURA: Can you cast little Restoration?

02:21:42.835 --> 02:21:46.723
MATT: You could also just give it a couple of
hours. Drink a lot of water.

02:21:46.723 --> 02:21:48.718
TRAVIS: What time is it?

02:21:48.718 --> 02:21:54.346
MATT: At this point, it's probably close to 3:00
in the afternoon.

02:21:54.346 --> 02:22:01.504
TRAVIS: So it's 3:00 in the afternoon. The bird
doesn't even come until night. We could let him

02:22:01.504 --> 02:22:03.706
wear it off.

02:22:03.706 --> 02:22:05.408
MARISHA: What time is it?

02:22:05.408 --> 02:22:08.069
SAM: 3:00. We just established this. We're going
to wait until night and go.

02:22:08.069 --> 02:22:11.746
LAURA: She said she hated you. How did that feel?

02:22:11.746 --> 02:22:18.183
LIAM: Fine. That was fine. That was the heat of
the moment. She was angry. We're a team.

02:22:18.183 --> 02:22:21.566
MATT: All right. What's the plan, guys?

02:22:21.566 --> 02:22:25.469
SAM: The plan is we're going to let him sober up.
We're going to give him some coffee. And then

02:22:25.469 --> 02:22:29.745
we're going to set off for the north farmlands at
dusk.

02:22:29.745 --> 02:22:35.371
ORION: Oh, we should get some corn and other
harvestments at the farms.

02:22:35.371 --> 02:22:38.625
MARISHA: I make an army of bears.

02:22:38.625 --> 02:22:40.683
MATT: &nbsp;Okay. This concentration will last an
hour.

02:22:40.683 --> 02:22:42.091
LAURA: Oh! That's it.

02:22:42.091 --> 02:22:43.670
MATT: The Conjure Woodland Beings?

02:22:43.670 --> 02:23:02.128
MARISHA: Wait! No! Hang on. What if I conjure a
bear, and then-- let me make sure, while they

02:23:02.128 --> 02:23:04.495
figure their stuff out. See, we're all figuring
stuff out?

02:23:04.495 --> 02:23:09.760
LAURA: What if I leave Trinket in the prison with
Jarett?

02:23:09.760 --> 02:23:12.717
TRAVIS: Yeah! That won't freak him out at all.

02:23:12.717 --> 02:23:17.734
SAM: Well, with Cordell. Jarett's down in the
cell. This is defense against invading vampires.

02:23:17.734 --> 02:23:21.247
MARISHA: Okay! I have a better idea!

02:23:21.308 --> 02:23:22.156
TRAVIS: Yep?

02:23:22.156 --> 02:23:23.684
SAM: Oh my god.

02:23:23.684 --> 02:23:30.277
MARISHA: Why don't I conjure an elemental, and
then I can cast Planar Binding on him and he'll

02:23:30.277 --> 02:23:31.908
hang out for 24 hours.

02:23:31.908 --> 02:23:36.180
SAM: Great! Do it. Make it done. Let's go kill a
bird.

02:23:36.180 --> 02:23:37.871
TRAVIS: Lead with that next time.

02:23:37.871 --> 02:23:40.647
MARISHA: I was figuring it out. It's new.

02:23:40.647 --> 02:23:42.282
SAM: You've got to talk it through.

02:23:42.282 --> 02:23:43.845
MARISHA: Figuring it out.

02:23:43.845 --> 02:23:45.154
TRAVIS: That's awesome!

02:23:45.154 --> 02:23:47.259
MATT: Yep! That'll do.

02:23:47.259 --> 02:23:50.592
TRAVIS: Don't vampires hate fire? Can you do fire?

02:23:50.592 --> 02:23:53.334
LAURA: Yeah, fire! Fire elemental!

02:23:53.334 --> 02:23:54.761
LIAM: Running water.

02:23:54.761 --> 02:23:57.788
LAURA: Ooh, water elemental! (gasps) Tiberius,
remember that you--

02:23:57.788 --> 02:23:58.891
TRAVIS: He's drunk!

02:23:58.891 --> 02:23:59.921
LAURA: I know.

02:23:59.921 --> 02:24:01.151
SAM: Don't talk to him.

02:24:01.151 --> 02:24:03.234
TRAVIS: He won't remember anything.

02:24:03.234 --> 02:24:06.043
ORION: (slurred) I love how you shoot arrows at
things' eyeballs.

02:24:06.043 --> 02:24:13.218
SAM: I use Minor Illusion to create Lockheed, and
I have him scamper away.

02:24:13.218 --> 02:24:18.576
ORION: Oh, that's you. But where are you going? You
go play up there. Tell your brother to be good.

02:24:18.576 --> 02:24:20.721
Anyway, you're so pretty.

02:24:20.721 --> 02:24:28.452
MATT: So are you doing that, Marisha? Keyleth, are
you summoning an elemental?

02:24:28.452 --> 02:24:29.739
MARISHA: Yes.

02:24:29.739 --> 02:24:31.409
MATT: Okay. Which kind?

02:24:31.409 --> 02:24:34.113
MARISHA: Water elemental.

02:24:34.113 --> 02:24:38.534
MATT: Okay. And you cast Planar Binding. Part of
the material component cost is a gem that's worth

02:24:38.534 --> 02:24:40.248
at least 1,000 gold pieces.

02:24:40.248 --> 02:24:42.341
TRAVIS: I have one of those.

02:24:42.341 --> 02:24:45.277
LAURA: You do?

02:24:45.277 --> 02:24:48.027
TRAVIS: Yeah. It's a jewel that's red and
palm-sized.

02:24:48.027 --> 02:24:53.832
LAURA: I have a diamond of awesome. And a regular
diamond, as well.

02:24:53.832 --> 02:25:02.334
LIAM: If I create a trap here, can you bind some
magic to it?

02:25:02.334 --> 02:25:08.863
ORION: You can do anything with magic. You can
make things go. You can make things stop.

02:25:08.863 --> 02:25:11.247
TRAVIS: I cover Tiberius's mouth again.

02:25:11.247 --> 02:25:12.865
LAURA: I give her a diamond.

02:25:12.865 --> 02:25:15.499
MATT: All right. Is this the awesome diamond or
the regular diamond?

02:25:15.499 --> 02:25:18.864
LAURA: This is a regular diamond. The awesome
diamond is special.

02:25:18.864 --> 02:25:20.418
MATT: All right.

02:25:20.418 --> 02:25:23.990
LAURA: No! Don't do that!

02:25:23.990 --> 02:25:26.082
MARISHA: I know! Why do you do that?

02:25:26.082 --> 02:25:29.429
LAURA: Diamonds are really expensive! Any
diamonds!

02:25:29.429 --> 02:25:34.188
MARISHA: I know! And an awesome diamond has got to
be more than 1,000, so this time there's got to be

02:25:34.188 --> 02:25:38.845
at least 1,000. Grog, what kind of jewel do you
have?

02:25:38.845 --> 02:25:41.565
TRAVIS: It's a palm-sized ruby.

02:25:41.565 --> 02:25:43.438
MARISHA: A palm-sized ruby?

02:25:43.438 --> 02:25:45.866
TRAVIS: Yeah, I got a big palm!

02:25:45.866 --> 02:25:47.522
MARISHA: Tiberius.

02:25:47.522 --> 02:25:49.726
SAM: No, just don't.

02:25:49.726 --> 02:26:00.886
MATT: Vex. Your keen eye is able to ascertain that
the palm-sized ruby is worth roughly 1,200 gold

02:26:00.886 --> 02:26:03.818
pieces and would be suitable for this ritual.

02:26:03.818 --> 02:26:08.505
LAURA: I think we should use the ruby. Because I
have an eye for these things.

02:26:08.505 --> 02:26:13.050
TRAVIS: Do we think they're going to come while we
do this? Do we want to waste it? Because that's an

02:26:13.050 --> 02:26:20.365
awesome outside defense. Do we want to waste it
for this? What if they're coming? Does it cost one

02:26:20.365 --> 02:26:21.695
jewel per--

02:26:21.695 --> 02:26:22.752
MATT: Yeah.

02:26:22.752 --> 02:26:26.126
TRAVIS: Maybe we should save that, because that's
awesome!

02:26:26.126 --> 02:26:34.173
LIAM: Is there a possibility, DM, that I could--
if he's sobered up-- if I set a trap, that a spell

02:26:34.173 --> 02:26:38.419
of his could be bound to it, somehow, and go off?
I have no idea.

02:26:38.419 --> 02:26:46.188
MATT: It's hard to say. There are certain spells
that can enable that. That can take certain spells

02:26:46.188 --> 02:26:51.432
that trigger at a certain time. Nothing that's
particularly in your guys' realm of experience or

02:26:51.432 --> 02:26:53.104
understanding though, unfortunately.

02:26:53.104 --> 02:26:55.212
LIAM: All right. So I can look into it for the
future, but not today.

02:26:55.212 --> 02:26:58.963
TRAVIS: Keyleth, I like that. I think we should
keep it in case there is an actual attack coming.

02:26:58.963 --> 02:27:03.000
Because it might just, 24 hours and then we waste
it. Nobody came.

02:27:03.000 --> 02:27:08.302
MARISHA: That's true. To be fair, the castle's
being heavily watched by outsiders, as well.

02:27:08.302 --> 02:27:12.350
SAM: Okay! Listen. Let's just go.

02:27:12.350 --> 02:27:17.604
ORION: Grog is big. Scanlan's small. Everything is
great. Hi.

02:27:17.604 --> 02:27:20.497
LIAM: Can we leave Trinket? To watch.

02:27:20.497 --> 02:27:24.169
LAURA: What? He's going to go down in the prison
with Jarett.

02:27:24.169 --> 02:27:31.627
MATT: Okay. You bring Trinket down. Trinket stands
watch right in the center, plops down right up

02:27:31.627 --> 02:27:32.887
against the bars.

02:27:32.887 --> 02:27:35.384
LAURA: I knock on Percy's door and say, Percy?

02:27:35.384 --> 02:27:37.084
MATT: "Yes?"

02:27:37.084 --> 02:27:43.327
LAURA: Trinket's out here. If you need anything,
you just come out and you pet him.

02:27:43.327 --> 02:27:45.964
MATT: "Thank you."

02:27:45.964 --> 02:27:47.571
LAURA: Welcome.

02:27:47.571 --> 02:27:51.885
ORION: I also go up to the door and go, Trinket.
(mumbling) Percy.

02:27:51.885 --> 02:27:54.038
LAURA: Aren't you sober yet?

02:27:54.038 --> 02:27:57.054
ORION: No, it's been like five minutes, hasn't
it?

02:27:57.054 --> 02:28:04.443
MATT: Yeah. Over time, over the next two to three
hours or so, you guys have set up a place to go.

02:28:04.443 --> 02:28:07.671
They have given you some water, and you've managed
to sober up a bit.

02:28:07.671 --> 02:28:11.988
LIAM: I actually picked his pocket and took his
bottle of endless water. Don't you have a bottle

02:28:11.988 --> 02:28:13.326
of water like that?

02:28:13.326 --> 02:28:19.203
MATT: No. That is currently left to be blessed for
holy water.

02:28:19.203 --> 02:28:21.825
LIAM: Oh. Oh, well.

02:28:21.825 --> 02:28:27.624
TRAVIS: And we take the scenic route to let him
walk it off as we head up towards Big Bird's

02:28:27.624 --> 02:28:29.496
house.

02:28:29.496 --> 02:28:30.987
SAM: Great!

02:28:30.987 --> 02:28:38.046
MATT: All right. So. You guys make your way around
the outskirts of Emon under moonlight. It's a

02:28:38.046 --> 02:28:46.792
three-quarter waxing moon. You make your way to
the farm vicinity on the north side of the city.

02:28:46.792 --> 02:28:52.592
It doesn't take long for you to eventually suss
out the house that matches the description that

02:28:52.592 --> 02:28:59.756
you were given by the Klauses. You knock on the
door, and they eagerly greet your arrival and

02:28:59.756 --> 02:29:08.732
invite you in. "So glad you all could make it.
Have you decided? Have you given our community's

02:29:08.732 --> 02:29:11.641
"request some thought?"

02:29:11.641 --> 02:29:14.880
SAM: We're here to help. We're the heroes that you
asked for.

02:29:14.880 --> 02:29:16.393
TRAVIS: We love old people.

02:29:16.393 --> 02:29:24.649
MATT: "Thank you. That's really good of you. We
will happily provide you with fresh produce, going

02:29:24.649 --> 02:29:28.265
"forward. We've talked to a few of the members of
the community and we're going to make sure that's

02:29:28.265 --> 02:29:29.358
"taken care of."

02:29:29.358 --> 02:29:33.315
SAM: Where do you think we should stake out this
bird? Where are your livestock kept?

02:29:33.315 --> 02:29:39.302
MATT: "The livestock are kept on the eastern side
of this community. If you look about, say about

02:29:39.302 --> 02:29:47.432
"half a mile out to where the actual residences
stop being clustered together, you'll see there

02:29:47.432 --> 02:29:54.585
"are a number of large livestock containment areas.
Hard to miss out there. We have pens for sheep; we

02:29:54.585 --> 02:30:01.132
"have pens for cows; we have pens for horses, other
beasts of burden. That whole vicinity is where

02:30:01.132 --> 02:30:05.278
"most of these attacks seem to be coming. So that's
probably your best bet there."

02:30:05.278 --> 02:30:08.045
LIAM: And the biggest you have are the bulls, you
said?

02:30:08.045 --> 02:30:12.211
MATT: "Bulls. We have a few big cows, as well.
We've lost a few of them, unfortunately."

02:30:12.211 --> 02:30:17.284
TRAVIS: That'll be all we need.

02:30:17.284 --> 02:30:21.827
LAURA: Can one of us polymorph into a giant cow?

02:30:21.827 --> 02:30:23.319
SAM: Sure.

02:30:23.319 --> 02:30:27.282
MARISHA: I could also talk to cows again. Maybe
these cows will know something.

02:30:27.282 --> 02:30:30.788
TRAVIS: We head out to the pasture.

02:30:30.788 --> 02:30:36.045
MARISHA: First can I ask her, you said your
neighbor boy, Kyle?

02:30:36.045 --> 02:30:40.307
SAM: Kyle. The neighbor boy. The neighbor boy's
son. Yes.

02:30:40.307 --> 02:30:43.483
MATT: "That's true. Kyle's the one who originally
spotted it, yeah."

02:30:43.483 --> 02:30:45.366
MARISHA: Where does he live?

02:30:45.366 --> 02:30:51.139
MATT: "He's actually the son of the man who runs
most of the livestock areas over there. You can go

02:30:51.139 --> 02:30:54.343
"and head over there. He's probably still up,
keeping his eye out in case it comes back."

02:30:54.343 --> 02:30:56.460
MARISHA: Thank you. I go to Kyle.

02:30:56.460 --> 02:31:03.333
MATT: Okay. You guys make your way over there.
It's easy to find. There's large pens. You can see

02:31:03.333 --> 02:31:09.157
that for as big as the pens are built and their
structure, they are noticeably dwindled. You can

02:31:09.157 --> 02:31:13.960
see why there's been some worry in the community
here. The fact that it's only been two weeks and

02:31:13.960 --> 02:31:22.120
this many creatures are gone is a little
disconcerting. As you get there, you can see the

02:31:22.120 --> 02:31:28.363
house has its light on. There are glowing windows.
And sitting in a chair, holding a crossbow across

02:31:28.363 --> 02:31:40.042
his lap, you see a 19-year-old boy, rugged chin
growth, dirty red hair that's disheveled. And he's

02:31:40.042 --> 02:31:44.570
sitting there looking around in the sky. Rocking
back and forth in his chair as you approach. "Who

02:31:44.570 --> 02:31:45.667
"goes there?"

02:31:45.667 --> 02:31:51.448
SAM: Don't worry, we're friends. We're friends of
the Klauses. Mr. and Mrs. Klaus.

02:31:51.448 --> 02:31:55.497
MATT: "Okay. Okay. So you the ones they say was
coming to help?"

02:31:55.497 --> 02:31:56.848
MARISHA: Yes.

02:31:56.848 --> 02:31:58.201
TRAVIS: Aye.

02:31:58.201 --> 02:31:59.901
LAURA: We hear you have a keen eye, Kyle.

02:31:59.901 --> 02:32:03.091
