ORION: 17.

02:46:15.719 --> 02:46:24.325
MATT: 17. That is an 18. Rolled a natural 18 on
that one. As it swoops down, you release the spell,

02:46:24.325 --> 02:46:37.468
you are immediately attempting to be grasped in
its talons. That is a 23 to hit.

02:46:37.468 --> 02:46:39.334
MARISHA: That hits.

02:46:39.334 --> 02:46:45.576
MATT: All right. So you then take 23 points of
slashing damage to your cow form.

02:46:45.576 --> 02:46:48.503
LAURA: I thought we were just--

02:46:48.503 --> 02:46:53.883
MATT: Oh. Okay. Sorry. You're not in cow form, are
you? You're illusioned. You're staying normal?

02:46:53.883 --> 02:46:55.383
MARISHA: No, I'm normal.

02:46:55.383 --> 02:46:59.568
MATT: You're normal. Right. Okay. I thought you
were saying you were doing an actual cow form, but

02:46:59.568 --> 02:47:06.100
no. All right. You take 23 points of slashing
damage, and you are currently grappled as it takes

02:47:06.100 --> 02:47:09.822
right back up into the air, clutching Keyleth
within its talons.

02:47:09.822 --> 02:47:11.933
LIAM: How fast can the rest of us do anything?
It's gone?

02:47:11.933 --> 02:47:16.746
MATT: Now you guys can react. It is currently 60
feet away from you.

02:47:16.746 --> 02:47:21.084
LAURA: I immediately-- oh god! I shoot it.

02:47:21.084 --> 02:47:24.917
SAM: Do we have to roll for initiative?

02:47:24.917 --> 02:47:26.272
MATT: You do.

02:47:26.272 --> 02:47:29.742
LAURA: But I was notched already.

02:47:29.742 --> 02:47:36.199
MATT: Right. I'll give you advantage on your
initiative. Because you're notched but you used

02:47:36.199 --> 02:47:42.615
your last turn to cast Hunter's Mark on it.
Everyone roll initiative. You have advantage on it

02:47:42.615 --> 02:47:45.515
because you were nocked, and because you were
ready to react, you have advantage on your

02:47:45.515 --> 02:47:56.712
initiative check, but everyone else just roll
normally. All right. So that is 25 to 20?

02:47:56.712 --> 02:47:57.945
LAURA: 21.

02:47:57.945 --> 02:47:59.307
MATT: 21.

02:47:59.307 --> 02:48:00.659
MATT: 20 to 15?

02:48:00.659 --> 02:48:01.835
LIAM: 17.

02:48:01.835 --> 02:48:02.786
TRAVIS: 18.

02:48:02.786 --> 02:48:04.081
MARISHA: 16.

02:48:04.081 --> 02:48:12.365
MATT: Vax. Keyleth. Scanlan? Tiberius? What you
guys got?

02:48:12.365 --> 02:48:13.510
SAM: Six.

02:48:13.510 --> 02:48:15.485
ORION: Five.

02:48:15.485 --> 02:48:19.794
MATT: Okay. All right. So Vex, you're up first.

02:48:19.794 --> 02:48:23.405
LAURA: I'm going to shoot it through the Blazing
Bowstring.

02:48:23.405 --> 02:48:25.825
MATT: Okay. Go for it. Roll for the attack.

02:48:25.825 --> 02:48:30.342
LAURA: 16.

02:48:30.342 --> 02:48:32.362
MATT: 16 hits.

02:48:32.362 --> 02:48:46.429
LAURA: (counts quietly) 26.

02:48:46.429 --> 02:48:49.700
MATT: 26 points of damage. All righty.

02:48:49.700 --> 02:48:52.371
LAURA: And then I'm going to shoot it again.

02:48:52.371 --> 02:48:53.798
MATT: Go for it.

02:48:53.798 --> 02:48:56.141
LAURA: That one definitely hits: 26.

02:48:56.141 --> 02:48:57.868
MATT: Yeah! That hits.

02:48:57.868 --> 02:49:06.206
LAURA: 26 again.

02:49:06.206 --> 02:49:10.784
MATT: Nice! All right, that brings us to Grog.

02:49:10.784 --> 02:49:16.556
TRAVIS: I take the Firebrand Warhammer, activate
it, turn on the fire. And I put the Chain of

02:49:16.556 --> 02:49:20.263
Returning on it and throw it at the winged beast.

02:49:20.263 --> 02:49:27.862
MATT: Okay. Go ahead and roll with disadvantage
because it's already roughly 40 to 60 feet away

02:49:27.862 --> 02:49:32.399
from you. It's tough to get there. But you can
try.

02:49:32.399 --> 02:49:42.917
TRAVIS: 15. Nope. 16.

02:49:42.917 --> 02:49:50.429
MATT: Okay. Due to its distance and the dark cover
of night, it's harder to hit and you actually

02:49:50.429 --> 02:49:55.100
swing and throw it and the hammer-- The chain goes
taut and it just drops to the ground and it's just

02:49:55.100 --> 02:49:58.616
out of range of the hammer, as it escapes the
range it would have hit it with.

02:49:58.616 --> 02:49:59.857
TRAVIS: Can I pull it back?

02:49:59.857 --> 02:50:02.460
MATT: Yeah, go for it. That's easy enough, it's
not wedged in anything. You don't have to roll

02:50:02.460 --> 02:50:06.208
for it. All right, so that's your turn. Vax.

02:50:06.255 --> 02:50:12.864
LIAM: I'd like to use a bonus action to click
Boots of Haste together, and I think if I do that,

02:50:12.864 --> 02:50:15.277
I have two actions at that point, right?

02:50:15.277 --> 02:50:24.960
MATT: No. Well you do have an additional action
that can be used only to attack.

02:50:24.960 --> 02:50:30.110
LIAM: Just attack. So what I want to do is click
the Boots of Haste together, use the original

02:50:30.110 --> 02:50:36.527
action to run as far as I can towards the bird,
and then use my final action to sneak attack the

02:50:36.527 --> 02:50:41.474
thing since it's got Keyleth in its talons. That's
up to you.

02:50:41.474 --> 02:50:47.520
MATT: Okay. The sneak attack will not kick in
because Keyleth is not threatening the creature.

02:50:47.520 --> 02:50:54.181
But you go for the attacks. You rush up, you dash,
you get underneath it-- for a moment, because of

02:50:54.181 --> 02:50:59.017
the Boots of Haste, you keep speed with this
giant, darting creature. You, underneath, throw

02:50:59.017 --> 02:51:00.692
your daggers upward.

02:51:00.692 --> 02:51:04.460
LIAM: All right. It would just be one-- I mean if
I use the dash to run as far as I can, that would

02:51:04.460 --> 02:51:06.079
leave me with one attack probably?

02:51:06.079 --> 02:51:08.355
MATT: One attack and your bonus without the damage
bonus.

02:51:08.355 --> 02:51:11.698
LIAM: I'm trying to be a Boy Scout here. Wouldn't
the Boots of Haste clicking be the bonus action?

02:51:11.698 --> 02:51:18.865
Yeah. That is 22 to hit.

02:51:18.865 --> 02:51:20.071
MATT: That hits.

02:51:20.071 --> 02:51:22.504
LIAM: All right. And that's not a whole lot.

02:51:22.504 --> 02:51:26.064
MATT: What's the range increment on a dagger?

02:51:26.064 --> 02:51:27.696
LIAM: That's ten. Ten.

02:51:27.696 --> 02:51:28.717
MATT: Ten?

02:51:28.717 --> 02:51:29.773
LIAM: Yeah.

02:51:29.773 --> 02:51:34.327
MATT: Dagger. Roll again for disadvantage because
it's just within your secondary throwing range.

02:51:34.327 --> 02:51:36.997
LIAM: Oh yeah. Then I missed.

02:51:36.997 --> 02:51:50.458
MATT: Okay. It vanishes into the dark night ahead
of you. So yeah. That is gone. You still have your

02:51:50.458 --> 02:51:55.470
Belt of Returning, you just don't have your snake
belt. Yeah, don't worry guys. I saw the look on

02:51:55.470 --> 02:52:03.396
your face and I'm like, no, it's fine. It comes
back. Okay. Keyleth, you're up. You're currently

02:52:03.396 --> 02:52:10.068
grappled and held within the talons of this giant
bird. You see the entire ground below you.

02:52:10.068 --> 02:52:16.857
MARISHA: Judging by the fairly close up appearance
I have of him at this point, can I tell it is

02:52:16.857 --> 02:52:19.488
probably a "beast" nature?

02:52:19.488 --> 02:52:29.830
MATT: At the sheer size, it's hard to tell. You've
never encountered a beast of this size, but you do

02:52:29.830 --> 02:52:33.271
look up and you can see the talons that are
currently holding you in place and piercing the

02:52:33.271 --> 02:52:38.819
sides of your armor are bird-like talons. And you
do see a series of dark feathers coating the

02:52:38.819 --> 02:52:41.550
entire underbelly of this entity.

02:52:41.550 --> 02:52:46.877
MARISHA: Okay. I'm going to attempt to cast
Dominate Beast.

02:52:46.877 --> 02:52:49.395
MATT: Okay. All right.

02:52:49.395 --> 02:52:51.927
MARISHA: It has to make a wisdom saving throw.

02:52:51.927 --> 02:52:53.385
MATT: Okay.

02:52:53.385 --> 02:52:59.110
LAURA: Is your Enhance Ability still active? From
before?

02:52:59.110 --> 02:53:07.890
MATT: That's for ability checks. So you finish
casting the spell. Apparently, this entity is not

02:53:07.890 --> 02:53:09.713
affected by the spell.

02:53:09.713 --> 02:53:11.091
LIAM: Fuck-sticks.

02:53:11.091 --> 02:53:12.311
SAM: It's not a beast?

02:53:12.311 --> 02:53:21.639
MATT: It is not a beast. There's a fine line when
certain creatures of nature are altered by some

02:53:21.639 --> 02:53:27.193
sort of magical essence or their nature perhaps is
not natural at the get-go. Either they were

02:53:27.193 --> 02:53:31.131
created or over time they became something beyond
beast. This seems to fall under that category.

02:53:31.131 --> 02:53:35.801
MARISHA: That's my turn, right?

02:53:35.801 --> 02:53:39.854
MATT: That's your turn. That brings us to its
turn.

02:53:39.854 --> 02:53:44.770
MARISHA: Can I try and break the grapple as a
bonus action?

02:53:44.770 --> 02:53:52.963
MATT: That would be your action to try and break
the grapple. For this creature's turn, it does a

02:53:52.963 --> 02:53:57.758
full double dash of its full flight speed and is
about 250 feet away from you and completely out of

02:53:57.758 --> 02:54:05.500
your guys' reach. You see it (whoosh) up into the
sky, disappearing to the north, north-northwest

02:54:05.500 --> 02:54:09.448
area beyond Emon, carrying Keyleth in its claws.

02:54:09.448 --> 02:54:13.322
LIAM: Keyleth, just get out of its fucking hands
and fall. You can change. We'll catch you; we'll

02:54:13.322 --> 02:54:15.415
do something! Just fall.

02:54:15.415 --> 02:54:18.410
MATT: You're close enough where you can still hear
this, as the desperation kicks in and you

02:54:18.410 --> 02:54:22.586
realize-- seeing your whole party not even visible
at this point except a couple of dark dots in the

02:54:22.586 --> 02:54:26.176
low light of the night.

02:54:26.176 --> 02:54:27.628
SAM: Is it our turn yet?

02:54:27.628 --> 02:54:29.068
MATT: It now comes to Scanlan's turn.

02:54:29.068 --> 02:54:31.012
SAM: Okay. I Dimension Door.

02:54:31.012 --> 02:54:32.074
MATT: What's the range on Dimension Door?

02:54:32.074 --> 02:54:33.394
SAM: 500 feet.

02:54:33.394 --> 02:54:36.467
MATT: You-- and appear where? Where do you want to
appear?

02:54:36.467 --> 02:54:38.836
SAM: On it. On its back.

02:54:38.836 --> 02:54:48.813
MATT: Okay. You appear right on its back. You
immediately land and start sliding back as the

02:54:48.813 --> 02:54:53.132
wind is pushing on you. The feathers themselves,
due to the aerodynamic nature of its flight path;

02:54:53.132 --> 02:54:54.781
it's a lot of wind resistance against you.

02:54:54.781 --> 02:54:56.474
LIAM: Oh, make an acrobatics check.

02:54:56.474 --> 02:54:59.262
ORION: Shush! What the hell?!

02:54:59.262 --> 02:55:03.387
MATT: No, I was going there. Don't worry. That's
what it is. You need to go ahead and make an

02:55:03.482 --> 02:55:06.443
acrobatics check to see if you can maintain
balance on the back of this beast.

02:55:06.443 --> 02:55:09.716
LIAM: My intelligence is not six!

02:55:09.716 --> 02:55:12.220
SAM: 20!

02:55:12.220 --> 02:55:17.553
MATT: You manage to just, you tumble backward a
little bit. You grab a couple of feathers and get

02:55:17.553 --> 02:55:21.809
yourself just on the side underneath where the
wing meets part of the upper torso, where the wind

02:55:21.809 --> 02:55:25.869
resistance is the least amount, and you manage to
hold on. You are now clutching the back of this

02:55:25.869 --> 02:55:29.521
giant bird. That's your turn.

02:55:29.521 --> 02:55:35.850
SAM: Okay. As my bonus action, I will inspire
Keyleth. Right? She's right next to me?

02:55:35.850 --> 02:55:38.994
MARISHA: Scanlan? What the shit?

02:55:38.994 --> 02:55:47.641
SAM: (singing) The way you kick so much ass like
nobody else. The way you do animal things gets me

02:55:47.641 --> 02:55:57.093
overwhelmed. You don't know. You don't know you're
powerful. Oh. That's what makes you powerful.

02:55:57.093 --> 02:56:01.986
MATT: Due to the wind, you don't hear the last
line. It's too loud around it. However, you can

02:56:01.986 --> 02:56:03.647
take a d10 inspiration dice.

02:56:03.647 --> 02:56:05.203
LAURA and MARISHA: Yay!

02:56:05.203 --> 02:56:08.631
LIAM: What a heroic move! Amazing!

02:56:08.631 --> 02:56:14.064
MATT: Which for the record, this currently right
now looks like-- you see the cow clutched below,

02:56:14.064 --> 02:56:18.969
and currently there is a cow holding onto this
giant bird.

02:56:18.969 --> 02:56:20.544
SAM: It lasts eight hours.

02:56:20.544 --> 02:56:24.846
MATT: This singing tiny cow. You artists out
there, have fun with this scene.

02:56:24.846 --> 02:56:28.438
(laughter)

02:56:28.438 --> 02:56:31.109
MATT: All right. That ends your turn. Tiberius.

02:56:31.109 --> 02:56:41.496
ORION: Good. I drop Stoneskin. At 5th-level, I go
myself, one, two, three-- I cast Fly on all of us.

02:56:41.496 --> 02:56:45.346
Fly, you fools! And go right after them.

02:56:45.346 --> 02:56:49.433
MATT: All right. All of you guys, at that point
you see Tiberius and you all take off after him.

02:56:49.433 --> 02:56:53.845
LIAM: The cows take off into the night sky.

02:56:53.845 --> 02:56:58.274
ORION: (shouting) Fly, Vox Machina! Moo!

02:56:58.274 --> 02:57:02.048
MARISHA: Vox "Moo-china!"

02:57:02.048 --> 02:57:04.128
(booing)

02:57:04.128 --> 02:57:10.760
MATT: A squadron of weirdly-sized, flying cows lit
by moonlight, chasing after a giant bird. I love

02:57:10.760 --> 02:57:12.248
Dungeons and Dragons.

02:57:12.248 --> 02:57:16.104
(laughter)

02:57:16.104 --> 02:57:17.693
TRAVIS: What is this?

02:57:17.693 --> 02:57:19.626
MATT: What's the flying speed on Fly?

02:57:19.626 --> 02:57:20.904
ORION: 60 feet.

02:57:20.904 --> 02:57:22.073
MATT: 60 feet. Cool.

02:57:22.073 --> 02:57:24.105
ORION: I'm going to dash. On that.

02:57:24.105 --> 02:57:30.954
MATT: Yep. You guys can go 120 feet every turn. It
can go 240. Two rounds pass before you guys

02:57:30.954 --> 02:57:33.968
realize there is no way you're going to catch up
with this thing or get even close to it.

02:57:33.968 --> 02:57:35.561
LIAM: I've got Haste!

02:57:35.561 --> 02:57:38.163
LAURA: I've got Hunter's Mark on it, so I can
track it.

02:57:38.163 --> 02:57:40.223
LIAM: Double me, yo! I got Haste.

02:57:40.223 --> 02:57:43.674
MATT: Your Haste speed-- your physical body
doesn't affect the Fly spell, unfortunately.

02:57:43.674 --> 02:57:51.191
You're only at the speed that the arcane nature of
the spell can take you. I'm just saying. Your

02:57:51.191 --> 02:57:54.475
metabolism's real fast. Your heartbeat's
hummingbirding it. But you're still only going 120

02:57:54.475 --> 02:58:02.737
feet. So as you guys follow behind, you can see
now, after a while on the edge of the shoreline,

02:58:02.737 --> 02:58:11.526
not too far from Emon-- maybe what would normally
be from horseback or a brisk walk, a half day's

02:58:11.526 --> 02:58:23.045
travel-- you eventually come upon the-- There it
is! You come upon the coastal mountains known as

02:58:23.045 --> 02:58:28.459
the Shoreline Summit. It's a series of unusually
steep mountain bluffs that hug the coastline,

02:58:28.459 --> 02:58:36.422
northwest of Emon. As you get closer, and at this
point you've lost sight of the bird. Scanlan, I

02:58:36.422 --> 02:58:39.817
want you to go ahead and roll an athletics check.

02:58:39.817 --> 02:58:50.654
SAM: Athletics? Well, that doesn't count.
That's not good. Athletics? 16.

02:58:50.654 --> 02:58:58.408
MATT: 16? Okay. You still manage to keep hold for
the portion of the length of the journey. As it

02:58:58.408 --> 02:59:02.513
moves and shifts and the wind itself is still
blowing in your face, though minimized by your

02:59:02.513 --> 02:59:08.793
current positioning. It's a trial to hold onto
this large creature as it makes its wings beat and

02:59:08.793 --> 02:59:14.253
just the sheer force of its movement. All right.
So as you get closer to these mountaintops--

02:59:14.253 --> 02:59:16.029
MARISHA: Do I have a turn yet?

02:59:16.029 --> 02:59:17.896
MATT: You can go ahead and take your turn now too,
yes.

02:59:17.896 --> 02:59:26.572
MARISHA: Yeah? I cast Polymorph on it. You're on
it.

02:59:26.572 --> 02:59:28.101
SAM: Don't worry about me!

02:59:28.101 --> 02:59:30.516
MARISHA: Really?

02:59:30.516 --> 02:59:37.814
SAM: I'm fine! You never need to worry about me.
Haven't you guys learned that by now? I'm fine!

02:59:37.814 --> 02:59:42.138
MARISHA: Out of thematic reasons, I also turn him
into a cow.

02:59:42.138 --> 02:59:46.760
(laughter)

02:59:46.760 --> 02:59:49.354
SAM: That's amazing!

02:59:49.354 --> 02:59:52.044
LIAM: Is what she cries out heroically.

02:59:52.044 --> 02:59:55.944
MATT: Okay. What's the DC on this?

02:59:55.944 --> 03:00:02.240
MARISHA: My spell DC? 18.

03:00:02.240 --> 03:00:03.369
MATT: Rolled a one.

03:00:03.369 --> 03:00:07.138
(laughter)

03:00:07.138 --> 03:00:09.418
SAM: I'm a cow on a cow with a cow!

03:00:09.418 --> 03:00:22.186
MATT: So this giant flying bird-- Moo! And just
begins to plummet at an extremely fast speed. You

03:00:22.186 --> 03:00:28.945
both immediately are released from its grasp.
Scanlan and Keyleth both are just falling. You

03:00:28.945 --> 03:00:33.064
guys don't see this. It's too far away from you
now. At this point, you're probably close to about

03:00:33.064 --> 03:00:36.459
500 feet in the air.

03:00:36.459 --> 03:00:39.957
LIAM: Yo, I heard you liked cows, so I gave you
some cows with your cow.

03:00:39.957 --> 03:00:46.566
MATT: I hope this inspires the next Diablo Cow
level, guys. You really need to look into this.

03:00:46.566 --> 03:00:54.195
All right. So you guys are now both plummeting and
falling at a really, really rapid speed.

03:00:54.195 --> 03:00:56.315
MARISHA: I go eagle form.

03:00:56.315 --> 03:01:00.984
MATT: Flailing cows. You go eagle form. You're
fine. So you go into eagle form. That's your

03:01:00.984 --> 03:01:03.443
action this turn. That's your bonus action,
because you can do that as a--

03:01:03.443 --> 03:01:04.869
MARISHA: As a bonus action!

03:01:04.869 --> 03:01:15.840
MATT: Eagle form. Scanlan, you plummet full speed
on this one. You probably have another two rounds

03:01:15.840 --> 03:01:18.223
before you impact with something very painful.

03:01:18.223 --> 03:01:21.980
LIAM: But he's as heavy as a dust mote, so he just
goes like this all the way down. Right?

03:01:21.980 --> 03:01:23.943
MARISHA: I don't think that's how it works.

03:01:23.943 --> 03:01:25.746
ORION: No, he's a little pebble.

03:01:25.746 --> 03:01:28.935
MARISHA: I can catch him, if you need catched.

03:01:28.935 --> 03:01:32.074
MATT: You guys still continue to give chase.
Eventually, you see this giant thing just go and

03:01:32.074 --> 03:01:35.724
vanish from sight. It's just gone. It just
disappeared.

03:01:35.724 --> 03:01:37.409
ORION: I go full Gandalf.

03:01:37.409 --> 03:01:39.086
MATT: All right.

03:01:39.086 --> 03:01:40.676
LIAM: Never go full Gandalf.

03:01:40.676 --> 03:01:46.727
MATT: You guys are pushing forward. So it's now
the next round for you guys to react. What are you

03:01:46.727 --> 03:01:48.087
doing?

03:01:48.087 --> 03:01:50.054
SAM: I will become a pterodactyl.

03:01:50.054 --> 03:01:51.336
MATT: So you're casting?

03:01:51.336 --> 03:01:52.786
SAM: Polymorph on myself?

03:01:52.786 --> 03:01:59.648
MATT: Okay. Because you are falling and this is a
lot of wind, I'm going to have to ask you to make

03:01:59.648 --> 03:02:02.090
a concentration check to complete the spell.

03:02:02.090 --> 03:02:03.847
LAURA: Come on, Scanlan!

03:02:03.847 --> 03:02:05.391
MATT: So go ahead and roll a d20.

03:02:05.391 --> 03:02:09.401
SAM: This is a concentration not on holding a
spell, but on casting it?

03:02:09.401 --> 03:02:13.375
MATT: Correct. Because as part of the
components of it and maintaining your attention to

03:02:13.375 --> 03:02:14.579
the spell--

03:02:14.579 --> 03:02:17.006
MARISHA: What does he add? His spell attack
bonus?

03:02:17.006 --> 03:02:24.859
MATT: This? No, this is a d20 and-- let me make
sure, yeah-- it's a d20 and then you add your plus

03:02:24.859 --> 03:02:28.481
five from your charisma.

03:02:28.481 --> 03:02:32.704
SAM: Charisma? That's a natural 20.

03:02:32.704 --> 03:02:34.565
(cheering)

03:02:34.565 --> 03:02:40.773
MATT: With that-- (screeches) pterodactyl.

03:02:40.773 --> 03:02:46.762
LIAM: Tables have turned, motherfucker! Tables
have turned!

03:02:46.762 --> 03:02:48.529
ORION: You're both flying cows!

03:02:48.529 --> 03:02:52.795
LAURA: Wait! Was Seeming a concentration?

03:02:52.795 --> 03:02:55.289
ORION: I think it lasts for like eight hours.

03:02:55.289 --> 03:02:57.363
LAURA: Did it drop? Are we no longer cows?

03:02:57.363 --> 03:03:00.060
SAM: I think so. I'll check.

03:03:00.060 --> 03:03:01.312
LIAM: Hey! You're not a cow anymore!

03:03:01.312 --> 03:03:02.901
LAURA: Oh my god, you're not a cow anymore!

03:03:02.901 --> 03:03:04.180
LIAM: Oh! Awesome!

03:03:04.180 --> 03:03:08.163
MATT: You guys keep flying. You guys catch yourselves.

03:03:08.163 --> 03:03:11.019
SAM: Nope, not concentration. It just lasts for
eight hours.

03:03:11.019 --> 03:03:16.156
MATT: You guys are all still flying cows. You're
all still just a squadron of flying, illusory

03:03:16.156 --> 03:03:24.631
cows, which you guys are both now transformed into
an eagle and a pterodactyl, but you still look

03:03:24.631 --> 03:03:25.575
like cows.

03:03:25.575 --> 03:03:27.508
(laughter)

03:03:27.508 --> 03:03:34.763
LIAM: As the twins are flying, I say, hey, did you
notice we have the same pattern? Twins!

03:03:34.763 --> 03:03:47.070
MATT: About this time, you hear a loud, impactful
boom. And there's a cloud of dust partway into

03:03:47.070 --> 03:03:51.895
the side of this first bit of mountain range that
you come upon, a little bit distant from you

03:03:51.895 --> 03:03:52.862
guys.

03:03:52.862 --> 03:03:54.189
LAURA: Can I fly down towards it?

03:03:54.189 --> 03:03:57.455
MATT: You start heading in that direction. Because
of the speed it was traveling at and the way it

03:03:57.455 --> 03:04:02.748
was carrying at the speed it was going, it's still
ahead of you guys. And you see the impact. You

03:04:02.748 --> 03:04:08.429
hear this loud screeching sound and you see now
where there was a little poof of cloud, these wings

03:04:08.429 --> 03:04:13.737
unfold and (flapping) make its way back up.

03:04:13.737 --> 03:04:15.829
ORION: How far away from it are we?

03:04:15.829 --> 03:04:21.485
MATT: You guys right now at the close to six
minutes you've been traveling--

03:04:21.485 --> 03:04:23.729
MARISHA: Did it not drop the cow to 0 hit points?

03:04:23.729 --> 03:04:27.697
MATT: All the damage carries over.

03:04:27.697 --> 03:04:32.842
LIAM: The remainder of that damage went into its
hit points.

03:04:32.842 --> 03:04:36.471
MATT: You don't know. It looks hurt. It looks like
it wasn't happy about it. It continues back up.

03:04:36.471 --> 03:04:41.809
From you Tiberius, it's probably close to 700 to
800 feet away from you. It's because of the speed

03:04:41.809 --> 03:04:45.015
it was traveling and the speed you guys were
following. It was gaining on you every single

03:04:45.015 --> 03:04:45.738
turn.

03:04:45.738 --> 03:04:46.874
LAURA: Is it flying away from us now?

03:04:46.874 --> 03:04:48.683
MATT: It's heading up into the mountain range.

03:04:48.683 --> 03:04:52.020
LIAM: Fly after that motherfucker!

03:04:52.020 --> 03:04:54.544
LAURA: Should we still track it? It's still
nighttime, right?

03:04:54.544 --> 03:04:56.061
MATT: It's still nighttime, yeah.

03:04:56.061 --> 03:04:57.692
ORION: It's only 500 feet away from me right now?

03:04:57.692 --> 03:04:59.074
MATT: 600 to 500 feet.

03:04:59.074 --> 03:05:00.793
ORION: Okay, cool. Well I'm going for it, still.

03:05:00.793 --> 03:05:02.183
MATT: What are you doing?

03:05:02.183 --> 03:05:03.668
LAURA: We're all following it.

03:05:03.668 --> 03:05:07.281
ORION: Where am I? It's taking off right now and
I'm over here?

03:05:07.281 --> 03:05:12.612
MATT: You're back here. It's now starting to take
off and head up towards the top of this mountain

03:05:12.612 --> 03:05:14.341
range that you're just starting to come upon.

03:05:14.341 --> 03:05:23.296
ORION: Okay. If it's doing that, then I'll fucking
go higher and try to meet it where it's going.

03:05:23.296 --> 03:05:31.797
MATT: Okay. Cool. The rest of you guys continue to
give chase. Now that it's returned to its form, it

03:05:31.797 --> 03:05:41.606
travels an additional double dash: 240 feet. As
this progresses, it's far beyond any of you guys

03:05:41.606 --> 03:05:42.635
in a matter of seconds.

03:05:42.635 --> 03:05:44.233
LAURA: Is the mountain range really far away?

03:05:44.233 --> 03:05:47.418
MATT: No, you've just hit the outskirts of the
mountain range. It got there first. You guys just

03:05:47.418 --> 03:05:51.117
catch up to where it starts and you see it's like
now it's dodging through the mountains and is

03:05:51.117 --> 03:05:55.640
currently no longer in sight. There is a little
bit of low cloud cover in this area. A couple

03:05:55.640 --> 03:05:59.963
drift by and cover a couple of the mountains. But
this little cluster of seaside cliffs and

03:05:59.963 --> 03:06:06.254
mountains, as you get closer, you can see it's
dotted with high altitude trees. There's

03:06:06.254 --> 03:06:09.812
precariously perched goats that are sleeping on
elements of the sides of this mountain.

03:06:09.812 --> 03:06:11.644
LIAM: Can you track it?

03:06:11.644 --> 03:06:13.975
LAURA: I can track it! Of course.

03:06:13.975 --> 03:06:15.766
MATT: So you're keeping your attention on it?

03:06:15.766 --> 03:06:16.938
LAURA: Yes.

03:06:16.938 --> 03:06:21.711
MATT: The winds also are pretty strong as you get
close to the mountains. As you coast around each,

03:06:21.711 --> 03:06:25.322
you start actually diving into this middle valley
area.

03:06:25.322 --> 03:06:27.253
LAURA: I'm going to cast Pass Without a Trace on
all of us.

03:06:27.253 --> 03:06:28.668
MATT: Okay.

03:06:28.668 --> 03:06:30.729
SAM: Does that affect any spells?

03:06:30.729 --> 03:06:32.524
LAURA: No, it just makes us stealth easier.

03:06:32.524 --> 03:06:33.777
SAM: It doesn't drop Hunter's Mark?

03:06:33.777 --> 03:06:34.929
MATT: Is it concentration?

03:06:34.929 --> 03:06:38.513
LAURA: No, it's not concentration; it's an action.
Oh wait. (laughs) I don't know if I can tell.

03:06:38.513 --> 03:06:40.388
MATT: Is Pass Without a Trace concentration?

03:06:40.388 --> 03:06:41.963
LAURA: Where does it say it?

03:06:41.963 --> 03:06:44.333
SAM: There's a C next to it somewhere.

03:06:44.333 --> 03:06:51.423
LAURA: Oh, never mind! It's a concentration. Forget
it! I don't know how these things work yet.

03:06:51.423 --> 03:06:53.858
SAM: Yeah, stick to the bows and arrows.

03:06:53.858 --> 03:06:57.447
MATT: Traveling through this area, you can see the
mountains. The way that they're constructed in

03:06:57.447 --> 03:07:00.795
this area, it's not a gradual crag. A lot of these
are just punched up in the air, like whatever

03:07:00.795 --> 03:07:07.087
heavy seismic force that created these initially
was very localized and very powerful. A lot of the

03:07:07.087 --> 03:07:11.137
mountains are spire-like. They come up with very
sheer sides and you can see why this mountain

03:07:11.137 --> 03:07:17.740
range is largely not utilized or traversed or
generally spoken of often because it's too

03:07:17.740 --> 03:07:23.719
dangerous for most average folk to even attempt to
climb or use for any good reason. The winds are

03:07:23.719 --> 03:07:28.158
high and powerful here at the tops, as well. And
as you're flying around, the winds blowing across,

03:07:28.158 --> 03:07:32.538
and you get pushed off your course a little bit
here and there, but you still keep up, best as

03:07:32.538 --> 03:07:39.653
possible. You leading the charge. Over about five
minutes of searching through this mountain range,

03:07:39.653 --> 03:07:42.872
you sense that its movement eventually comes to
stop.

03:07:42.872 --> 03:07:44.536
LAURA: Okay.

03:07:44.536 --> 03:07:46.187
TRAVIS: There's a nest.

03:07:46.187 --> 03:07:48.872
SAM: Wait, you sense that he came to a stop?

03:07:48.872 --> 03:07:51.730
LAURA: He came to a stop a little bit ahead of
us.

03:07:51.730 --> 03:07:54.224
SAM: Let's go get him.

03:07:54.224 --> 03:07:57.140
LAURA: Can we all try to stealth in?

03:07:57.140 --> 03:08:00.175
SAM: I'm a pterodactyl, so--

03:08:00.175 --> 03:08:02.729
MARISHA: Yeah, let's go for the element of
surprise. Well, technically, we're all still

03:08:02.729 --> 03:08:03.967
cows.

03:08:03.967 --> 03:08:07.818
MATT: Yes. And you guys cannot talk because you're
actually in creature forms.

03:08:07.818 --> 03:08:14.009
LAURA: All right. Well, I'm going to try to
stealth. Mountains are my favored terrain!

03:08:14.009 --> 03:08:19.202
MATT: They are! Do you want to go onto the
mountain itself, or are you still flying amongst

03:08:19.202 --> 03:08:19.995
them?

03:08:19.995 --> 03:08:21.583
LAURA: Oh, I'll still fly.

03:08:21.583 --> 03:08:26.955
MATT: So you would not get the advantage because
air is not your favored terrain. So everyone who

03:08:26.955 --> 03:08:29.275
wishes to, go ahead and roll stealth checks

03:08:29.275 --> 03:08:30.573
MARISHA: All of us?

03:08:30.573 --> 03:08:33.416
MATT: All of you who wish to try and come at it
from a quiet--

03:08:33.416 --> 03:08:36.489
SAM: (pterodactyl screech)

03:08:36.489 --> 03:08:40.518
MATT: What did you roll?

03:08:40.518 --> 03:08:43.130
LIAM: With advantage, I rolled a two.

03:08:43.130 --> 03:08:45.103
MATT: Okay.

03:08:45.103 --> 03:08:47.884
LIAM: I'm not used to being flying, really.

03:08:47.884 --> 03:08:51.163
SAM: Five.

03:08:51.163 --> 03:08:53.202
ORION: Are we flying anymore?

03:08:53.202 --> 03:08:54.965
MATT: You guys are all still flying, yeah.

03:08:54.965 --> 03:08:58.488
ORION: Oh, shit. Okay. Oh, no.

03:08:58.488 --> 03:09:00.126
MARISHA: 21.

03:09:00.126 --> 03:09:01.300
TRAVIS: 14.

03:09:01.300 --> 03:09:02.559
LAURA: 28.

03:09:02.559 --> 03:09:09.988
MATT: Yeah, so. You guys following behind Vex, many
of you clumsily and some of you shouting out to

03:09:10.047 --> 03:09:17.191
each other, "I think she sees it this way." And
you're like, "oh my god." You come around this one

03:09:17.191 --> 03:09:21.805
bend and you can see one of the larger mountainous
spires that has a lot of trees and green growth

03:09:21.805 --> 03:09:26.606
towards the top at certain places where the rock
juts out and gives a shelf for such greenery to

03:09:26.606 --> 03:09:34.490
grow, outside of its sheer outside surface. You do
see a couple of wings fold in against the

03:09:34.490 --> 03:09:39.384
moonlight in what looks to be an outcropping. And
there are multiple layers of rock shelves on the

03:09:39.384 --> 03:09:43.030
side of this mountain. And on one of these
outcroppings, there appears to be some sort of a

03:09:43.030 --> 03:09:50.367
nest: a cluster of almost like actual trees and
pieces of wood that are all jammed into this giant

03:09:50.367 --> 03:09:55.997
nest that's nestled against where the shadow and
the moonlight are fighting for some sort of visual

03:09:55.997 --> 03:09:57.179
on it.

03:09:57.179 --> 03:09:58.589
TRAVIS: Big-ass tree fortress.

03:09:58.589 --> 03:10:01.427
LAURA: Did we just find like a mama bird and baby
birds?

03:10:01.427 --> 03:10:03.042
MARISHA: Yeah, we did.

03:10:03.042 --> 03:10:04.466
LAURA: What are we going to do?

03:10:04.466 --> 03:10:07.090
LIAM: We're going to take out the mom and train
the babies.

03:10:07.090 --> 03:10:11.832
SAM: What are we going to do?

03:10:11.832 --> 03:10:15.380
LIAM: Yeah. We're going to capture those babies
and we're going to train them.

03:10:15.380 --> 03:10:18.815
ORION: That's a good idea. I like that idea.

03:10:18.815 --> 03:10:20.056
SAM: Like Avatar?

03:10:20.056 --> 03:10:21.350
ORION: Yes.

03:10:21.350 --> 03:10:23.261
TRAVIS: You could go in.

03:10:23.261 --> 03:10:27.832
LAURA: Me go in? There's a giant fucking nest
here! I get close to it. As close as I feel safe

03:10:27.832 --> 03:10:29.039
getting to it.

03:10:29.039 --> 03:10:30.828
MATT: You guys all stay back or do you go with
her?

03:10:30.828 --> 03:10:34.887
ORION: I'm going to cast Greater Invisibility on
myself and then follow.

03:10:34.887 --> 03:10:38.628
MATT: Okay. You guys have 12 seconds before you
all plummet.

03:10:38.628 --> 03:10:42.464
ORION: Oh wait! No! I don't do that. Damn it! I
forget we're still flying.

03:10:42.464 --> 03:10:46.263
TRAVIS: What part of the flying part did you
forget?

03:10:46.263 --> 03:10:48.261
ORION: I thought we'd landed already.

03:10:48.261 --> 03:10:52.793
MATT: Are you guys all going with Vex, or are you
all staying back and she's going on her own?

03:10:52.793 --> 03:10:54.605
TRAVIS: Are we going to lose Fly, or do we keep
it?

03:10:54.605 --> 03:10:56.390
MATT: Are you casting Greater Invisibility?

03:10:56.390 --> 03:10:57.383
ORION: No.

03:10:57.383 --> 03:10:58.948
MATT: Then no, you're fine.

03:10:58.948 --> 03:11:01.959
LIAM: Is it the same stealth roll or an additional
stealth roll to go forward at this point?

03:11:01.959 --> 03:11:03.815
MATT: No this was your stealth roll on
approaching.

03:11:03.815 --> 03:11:06.290
LIAM: Oh. Well, I mean, I knew I rolled
shitty.

03:11:06.335 --> 03:11:07.773
MATT: You don't know you rolled shitty.

03:11:07.773 --> 03:11:09.263
TRAVIS: I'm going in.

03:11:09.263 --> 03:11:18.202
MATT: All right. So Vex and Grog, you approach.
Gliding cows, drifting through the night sky.

03:11:18.202 --> 03:11:20.174
LAURA: This is so stupid.

03:11:20.174 --> 03:11:21.597
TRAVIS: Hoof in hoof.

03:11:21.597 --> 03:11:27.879
MATT: Okay, yeah. So you guys all realize you must
keep close together to Tiberius as you come in.

03:11:27.879 --> 03:11:33.815
Keeping too much of a distance would be a bad
thing. You come upon the underneath portion of

03:11:33.815 --> 03:11:39.099
this outcropping, and you can see within a quick
glance-- go ahead and make a perception check, all

03:11:39.099 --> 03:11:40.082
of you guys.

03:11:40.082 --> 03:11:41.263
MARISHA: All of us?

03:11:41.263 --> 03:11:43.680
MATT: All of you who are coming up in this
cluster.

03:11:43.680 --> 03:11:44.919
TRAVIS: Three.

03:11:44.919 --> 03:11:48.934
LAURA: Do I get an advantage because we're in a
mountain environment at all?

03:11:48.934 --> 03:11:52.990
MATT: Nope. Actually no. Because you're seeing
things on a mountain, I will give you advantage on

03:11:52.990 --> 03:11:53.821
this.

03:11:53.821 --> 03:11:54.691
LAURA: Yes!

03:11:54.691 --> 03:11:57.047
MARISHA: 12.

03:11:57.047 --> 03:11:58.340
MATT: 12?

03:11:58.340 --> 03:11:59.694
ORION: 16.

03:11:59.694 --> 03:12:01.118
SAM: Nothing.

03:12:01.118 --> 03:12:02.194
LIAM: 13.

03:12:02.194 --> 03:12:04.141
LAURA: 12.

03:12:04.141 --> 03:12:06.306
MATT: So the highest was?

03:12:06.306 --> 03:12:07.433
ORION: 16.

03:12:07.433 --> 03:12:09.931
MATT: 16. You got?

03:12:09.931 --> 03:12:11.029
TRAVIS: Three.

03:12:11.029 --> 03:12:16.927
MATT: As you guys all look up, it's very shadowy
over here. It's hard to see. The moonlight's in

03:12:16.927 --> 03:12:20.871
your eye a little bit and the darkness is so
pitch. The umbra of this particular shadow is very

03:12:20.871 --> 03:12:29.116
dark and crushed. You make out, in the nest, the
large bird creature has folded its wings and is

03:12:29.116 --> 03:12:36.057
currently leaning down. And you see something
in the nest that's much smaller moving up next to it.

03:12:36.057 --> 03:12:39.728
MARISHA: I don't want to kill a mama.

03:12:39.728 --> 03:12:42.983
LAURA: But she's killing the farmers' stuff.

03:12:42.983 --> 03:12:46.513
MARISHA: Maybe we can transplant her.

03:12:46.513 --> 03:12:50.322
SAM: To a wildlife preserve?

03:12:50.322 --> 03:12:52.381
LAURA: Maybe. And her babies?

03:12:52.381 --> 03:12:55.790
MARISHA: Capture her and move her away from town?

03:12:55.790 --> 03:12:58.854
LIAM: That seems complicated.

03:12:58.854 --> 03:13:01.389
SAM: Are they on the highest peak?

03:13:01.389 --> 03:13:06.187
MATT: No. There's two other levels up above this.
This one just is one of the largest outcroppings.

03:13:06.187 --> 03:13:11.501
SAM: I'm going to swoop up over them. See if
there's any boulders to drop.

03:13:11.501 --> 03:13:21.561
MATT: Okay. Looking over it, there are no loose
rocks or boulders. In fact, because of the

03:13:21.561 --> 03:13:26.314
construction of these mountains, they're solid
spires that jut up and then abruptly end. All the

03:13:26.314 --> 03:13:29.435
erosion that happens here appears to be gradual
enough-- that's why the sides of the mountains are

03:13:29.435 --> 03:13:31.360
so smooth and unclimbable.

03:13:31.360 --> 03:13:36.751
MARISHA: So there's a sheer peak and they're
nested on the side of it?

03:13:36.751 --> 03:13:39.975
MATT: Yeah. It's a sheer peak that rounds off at
the very top and there are little outcroppings

03:13:39.975 --> 03:13:43.609
that jut out in places as it goes down. But those
are more towards the top, and as you go down

03:13:43.609 --> 03:13:48.599
further-- as most of the erosion hits the mountain
lower and lower, it has carved off or destroyed

03:13:48.599 --> 03:13:52.524
most of what would have been previous outcroppings,
or smoothed them over.

03:13:52.524 --> 03:13:54.579
TRAVIS: How far away are we now?

03:13:54.579 --> 03:14:00.975
MATT: You guys are probably a good 60 or 50 feet
if you're trying to get up within range of your

03:14:00.975 --> 03:14:05.116
Fly. Right? What's the range of on that? Fly?

03:14:05.116 --> 03:14:11.628
SAM: Fly? Oh, here.

03:14:11.628 --> 03:14:22.409
MATT: I got it. No! There is no range on it. You
just touch them. So you're fine. Yeah. As long as

03:14:22.409 --> 03:14:24.051
you're concentrating on it, you're fine.

03:14:24.051 --> 03:14:26.731
TRAVIS: So we're within 60 feet?

03:14:26.731 --> 03:14:31.789
MATT: Well, you guys have been keeping a little
more of a distance down here. However, at this

03:14:31.789 --> 03:14:38.445
point, as you guys are all encroaching and
Scanlan's gone overhead, a voice rings out against

03:14:38.445 --> 03:14:51.539
the darkness, "Flying cows? Really? I care not for
this insolence. If you've come to mock me or fight

03:14:51.539 --> 03:14:56.864
"me, do it now! Or leave this creature alone!"

03:14:56.864 --> 03:15:02.964
LAURA: What? Where are you? Who are you? Who said
that?

03:15:02.964 --> 03:15:08.889
ORION: I rolled an arcana check of 17 of my
surroundings-- where it's coming from.

03:15:08.889 --> 03:15:11.492
LAURA: Ditto. I try to perceive where it's coming
from.

03:15:11.492 --> 03:15:16.039
MATT: Okay. Arcana check-- there's nothing arcane
in nature. It's not omnipresent or coming from any

03:15:16.039 --> 03:15:19.282
certain place. There is a direction it's coming
from, which is from the outcropping or nest area.

03:15:19.282 --> 03:15:26.699
There's nothing arcane in nature to it. It's in
the shadow. You can't really see it from this

03:15:26.699 --> 03:15:27.800
distance.

03:15:27.800 --> 03:15:30.054
LAURA: Is it in front of us? To the side of us? Is
it coming from where the bird seems to be?

03:15:30.054 --> 03:15:31.655
MATT: It's coming from where the bird is.

03:15:31.655 --> 03:15:33.539
LIAM: He's controlling it.

03:15:33.539 --> 03:15:39.615
MARISHA: I fly over as an eagle.

03:15:39.615 --> 03:15:43.016
LAURA: You still look like a cow eagle.

03:15:43.016 --> 03:15:44.500
MARISHA: Can we drop Seeming?

03:15:44.500 --> 03:15:48.997
MATT: It's not under your control, and you can't
talk, too.

03:15:48.997 --> 03:15:54.745
TRAVIS: Okay. I yell out, you've been stealing the
farmers' livestock. Give us a reason not to kill

